Air Jordan 1 Mid ALT TD 'Red Black Toe'
Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG co.JP 'Tokyo' Japan Release
results.story: The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG co.JP 'Tokyo' Japan Release makes use of a familiar color scheme that recalls a Japan-exclusive colorway from 2001. Unlike the original, the design replaces a Jumpman atop the tongue with Nike Air branding. The rest of the upper combines matte grey leather with a metallic silver finish on the toe box, Swoosh, heel and collar flap. The latter is adorned with a jeweled Jordan Wings logo on the sneaker’s lateral side.

results.name: Jordan React Elevation PF 'Chicago Bulls'
results.story: The Jordan React Elevation PF ‘Chicago Bulls’ applies a heritage color palette to a lightweight basketball shoe that recalls the Jordan Westbrook One Take. The white mesh upper is reinforced with a perforated leather saddle that’s integrated into the laces for midfoot containment. Split cushioning combines Nike React foam under the heel and a responsive Zoom Air unit in the forefoot. An extra-durable herringbone rubber outsole is made for play on outdoor courts.

results.name: Jordan Dub Zero TD 'Metallic Gold'
results.story: Made for toddlers, the Jordan Dub Zero TD ‘Metallic Gold’ showcases a familiar color scheme that recalls the legendary Defining Moments Pack from 2006. The retro-inspired design features an upper constructed from shiny black patent leather with white leather overlays finished in intricate laser-etched patterns. This version for little feet utilizes a two-tone foam midsole that lacks the visible Zoom Air cushioning of the original.

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG 'Bloodline 2.0'
results.story: A sequel to the November 2019 release, the Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG ‘Bloodline 2.0’ features the same color-blocking as the original, highlighted by a premium white leather base with contrasting red leather overlays. A black Nike Swoosh is complemented by matching black piping throughout the upper. Nike Air branding adorns the tongue tag and sockliner, while the Jordan Wings logo is stamped on the lateral collar flap.

results.name: Air Jordan 13 Retro 'Lucky Green'
results.story: The Air Jordan 13 Retro ‘Lucky Green’ makes use of a familiar design that calls to mind Ray Allen’s coveted Air ‘Three-Point Record’ PE from 2011. The upper combines white tumbled leather with green synthetic suede, supported underfoot by the silhouette’s signature panther paw outsole in black rubber. Branding hits include a green embroidered Jumpman atop the tongue, matching the circular hologram on the lateral ankle.

results.name: Jordan Westbrook One Take PF 'Mango Tint'
Jordan React Elevation PF 'White Hyper Violet'
Jordan Why Not Zer0.3 SE PF 'Flash Crimson'
Jordan Max 200 'Triple Black'
results.story: The Jordan Max 200 ‘Triple Black’ highlights a stealthy monochromatic finish on a retro-inspired silhouette that takes its cues from the Air Jordan 4. The lightweight upper, featuring translucent textile on the quarter panel and Nike Air branding on the heel, utilizes a flexible cage integrated into the lacing system for a stable and supportive fit. The mid-top rides on a soft foam midsole with a Max Air unit under the heel for superior cushioning.

results.name: Jordan Aerospace 720 JCRD 'White'
results.story: The Jordan Aerospace 720 JCRD ‘White’ delivers pillowy comfort with each step, thanks to a visible Max Air unit that runs the length of the rubber outsole. Up top, the lifestyle sneaker’s breathable knit construction is reinforced with a blend of no-sew skins and synthetic leather overlays. The neutral white and black color scheme is disrupted by a Jumpman logo in contrasting Gym Red embroidery atop the tongue.

results.name: Jordan Max Aura 2 'Black Cement'
results.story: The Jordan Max Aura 2 ‘Black Cement’ applies a familiar color scheme to a hoops shoe steeped in Jordan DNA. The upper, constructed from black ballistic mesh with a matching leather overlay, rides on a white foam midsole with a visible Max Air unit in the heel. A herringbone traction rubber outsole delivers optimal grip. Contrasting pops of Gym Red make their way to the sneaker’s interior lining and branding elements, including an embossed Jumpman atop the tongue.

results.name: Dior x Air Jordan 1 Low
results.story: Launching as part of a larger collection with the esteemed Parisian fashion house, the Dior x Air Jordan 1 Low sports a simple two-tone color scheme on the upper, featuring a white Italian leather base with subtle grey leather overlays. Branding elements include a Dior Air woven tongue tag, Dior Oblique jacquard Swoosh and a Dior Wings logo on the heel tab. The made-in-Italy kicks are finished with translucent outsoles revealing additional branding hits underneath.

results.name: Air Jordan 3 Retro SE 'Animal Instinct 2.0'
results.story: A sequel to the wildlife-inspired December 2019 colorway, the Air Jordan 3 Retro SE ‘Animal Instinct 2.0’ features a number of different exotic prints on the upper. They include a croc-textured black leather base, tonal ostrich-skin mudguard and grey snakeskin on the forefoot overlay. Mocha brown coloring on Jordan Brand’s iconic elephant print is contrasted by a bright yellow heel panel and scaly green collar.

results.name: Air Jordan 34 EP GS 'Heritage'
results.story: Made for big kids, the Air Jordan 34 EP GS ‘Heritage’ combines a lightweight, performance-ready build with familiar elements culled from legacy Jordan models. Translucent textile reveals an upper covered in an abstract multicolor design, while the heel panel superimposes an orange Jumpman atop grey elephant print. The sneaker rides on a speckled foam midsole, outfitted with a hollowed-out Eclipse Plate that reveals Zoom Air cushioning.

results.name: Jordan Delta SP 'Black'
results.story: Made for daily wear, the Jordan Delta SP ‘Black’ features a monochromatic finish on the upper, crafted from breathable mesh with suede overlays for added support and durability. A padded collar delivers a comfortable fit around the ankle, while pull loops at the tongue and heel provide easy on and off. The blacked-out design up top is countered by an Off-White React midsole, reinforced underfoot by a herringbone-tread rubber outsole.

results.name: SoleFly x Air Jordan 10 Retro '10th Anniversary'
results.story: Celebrating the Miami-based retailer’s first decade in business, the SoleFly x Air Jordan 10 Retro ‘10th Anniversary’ features a design inspired by Miami’s Freedom Tower. The all-suede upper, finished in Sail and beige coloring, recalls the structure’s two-tone façade, while a newsprint graphic on the outsole references the building’s origins as the headquarters of The Miami News. Unique branding hits include ‘SOLEFLY 10’ stamped on the tongue and the shop’s logo embroidered on the left heel.

results.name: Air Jordan 34 Low PF 'Heritage'
results.story: Riding atop a wear-resistant rubber outsole, the Air Jordan 34 Low PF ‘Heritage’ is specially made for play on outdoor courts. The upper, constructed from translucent black textile with tonal synthetic suede overlays, features reflective detailing for added visibility in low-light conditions. The tooling is unchanged from the inline 34, featuring a Zoom Air unit below the forefoot that’s visible through the Eclipse plate.

results.name: Air Jordan 34 Low 'Heritage'
results.story: The Air Jordan 34 Low ‘Heritage’ applies a familiar color scheme to the performance hoops shoe. The upper is constructed from a blend of semi-translucent black textile with matching black suede overlays at the toe and heel. An exposed padded collar distinguishes the low-top from its full-height counterpart, while the pull loop and layered tongue remain intact. The latter is embellished with silver Jumpman branding and a classic Flight logo in red.

results.name: Air Jordan 34 Low 'Heritage'
results.story: The Air Jordan 34 Low ‘Heritage’ gets dressed in a simple two-tone color scheme, executed on a build that’s mostly unchanged from the sneaker’s full-height counterpart. The upper, constructed from semi-translucent black textile, features a lower collar and an added suede toe cap. Laser Orange accents are applied to the tongue and heel panel, treated to a subtle iridescent finish and marked with a raised Jumpman logo in black.

results.name: Jordan Why Not Zer0.3 PF 'Black Cement'
Jordan Why Not Zer0.3 'Black Cement'
results.story: The Jordan Why Not Zer0.3 ‘Black Cement’ aspires to sneaker-design greatness, featuring an instantly familiar assemblage of colors and patterns that recall the iconic Air Jordan 3 release. Russell Westbrook’s third signature shoe utilizes a black mesh upper with Bright Crimson detailing and cement print overlays at the toe and heel, while Nike Air branding adorns the woven tag on the lateral side panel for an OG-inspired look.

results.name: Air Jordan 34 Low PF 'Pure Money'
results.story: Featuring an extra-durable rubber outsole made for outdoor courts, the Air Jordan 34 Low PF ‘Pure Money’ features a pristine color scheme inspired by the classic white-on-white Air Jordan 4 from 2006. This low-top edition is mostly unchanged from the inline 34, save for an exposed padded collar, synthetic leather toe cap and revised heel panel. Vibrant pops of Electric Green are mostly kept under wraps, appearing on the sockliner and rubber outsole

results.name: Air Jordan 34 Low 'Pure Money'
results.story: The Air Jordan 34 Low ‘Pure Money’ showcases a pristine color scheme that recalls the white-on-white Air Jordan 4 originally released in 2006. Here, the monochromatic finish is disrupted by a number of subtle accents, including black eyelets, metallic silver Jumpman branding and neon green detailing that seeps through the semi-translucent textile upper. Additional pops of bright green appear on the midsole and sockliner.

results.name: Air Jordan 6 Retro 'Hare'
results.story: The Air Jordan 6 Retro 'Hare' delivers an understated take on the classic silhouette with a championship pedigree. Monochromatic grey coloring is applied to the suede upper, appointed with traditional AJ6 details that include lace locks, perforated inlays and an extended spoiler at the heel. A two-tone midsole, finished in contrasting white and True Red tones, is supported by a translucent rubber outsole underfoot.

results.name: Jordan Why Not Zer0.3 PF 'Triple White'
results.story: The Jordan Why Not Zer0.3 ‘Triple White’ applies an immaculate finish to Russell Westbrook’s signature shoe. The all-white color scheme lessens the visual impact of the sneaker’s mixed-material build, highlighted by a breathable mesh base with synthetic leather overlays and an adjustable translucent midfoot strap. The matching white midsole, fitted with a large Air Zoom Turbo unit in the forefoot, is reinforced by a split outsole designed to reduce weight.

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Mid SE GS 'Clover'
results.story: Made for big kids, the Air Jordan 1 Mid SE GS 'Clover' updates the classic silhouette with vibrant colors and a unique graphic print. The latter showcases four-leaf clovers outlined in reflective 3M on the black leather quarter panel and toe box. The sneaker’s leather overlays are rendered in contrasting tones of neon green, orange and yellow, along with a Nike Swoosh in powder blue. A teal rubber outsole anchors the multicolor design.

results.name: Jordan Why Not Zer0.3 'Hearbeat'
results.story: The Jordan Why Not Zer0.3 ‘Heartbeat’ features a two-tone color scheme that honors Russell Westbrook’s twin daughters, with the pink accents modeled after the girls’ bedroom color. As for the shoe’s performance benefits, they’re specifically tuned to Russ’ kinetic style of play. Highlights include an adjustable midfoot strap for a lockdown fit and a large Air Zoom Turbo unit in the forefoot, curved to accommodate the natural contours of the foot.

results.name: Air Jordan 34 'Infrared 23'
results.story: The Air Jordan 34 ‘Infrared 23’ serves up a distinctive colorway with a championship pedigree. The design represents a flip on the ‘Infrared’ Air Jordan 6, the shoe that Michael wore in 1991 when he clinched his first ever NBA title. Here, the vibrant red hue acts as the sneaker’s base color, while contrasting black accents appear on the tongue, heel panel and midsole. ‘Flight’ and Nike Air branding strengthen the connection to Jordan Brand heritage.

results.name: Air Jordan 34 PF 'Infrared 23'
results.story: The Air Jordan 34 PF ‘Infrared 23’ boasts a championship pedigree, featuring the same combination of colors used on the Air Jordan 6 that Michael wore when he clinched his first NBA title back in 1991. Here, Infrared is the sneaker’s base color, as the bright crimson hue is applied liberally to both the mesh upper and midsole. Contrasting black accents appear on the tongue, collar and heel, the latter embellished with Nike Air branding for an OG-inspired touch.

results.name: Jordan Why Not Zer0.3 'LA Born'
results.story: Dropping as part of Nike’s 2020 NBA All-Star Collection, the Jordan Why Not Zer0.3 'LA Born' gives the nod to Russell Westbrook’s hometown. The ‘90s-inpired design features a white textile base with vibrant accents in royal blue, Racer Pink and Ghost Green. A translucent midfoot strap delivers a lockdown fit, while a split rubber outsole enhances flexibility while helping to reduce weight. Elephant print at the heel draws a connection to Jordan heritage.

results.name: Xbox One x Air Jordan 3 Retro SE 'Unite' Special Box
Air Ship x Air Jordan 1 'New Beginnings'
results.story: Released as one-half of the 'New Beginnings' Pack, the Nike Air Ship preceded the Air Jordan 1 as the silhouette that Michael Jordan wore at the start of his NBA career. The vintage high-top is clad in a white leather upper, accented with contrasting pops of Varsity Red at the padded collar and durable rubber outsole. The sneaker’s branding elements are similarly finished in crimson, including the leather Nike Swoosh and woven tongue tag.

results.name: Air Jordan 34 'Black Cat'
results.story: The Air Jordan 34 'Black Cat' draws direct inspiration from the namesake colorway of the Air Jordan 4, originally released in 2006 and inspired by one of Michael Jordan’s many nicknames. Like its antecedent, this pair features a monochromatic black finish throughout the exterior, save for subtle Electric Green accents on the herringbone rubber outsole. Additionally, reflective detailing throughout the upper shine bright during certain low-light conditions.

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Mid PS 'White Court Purple Teal'
results.story: Made for little kids, the Air Jordan 1 Mid PS ‘White Court Purple Teal’ utilizes a white leather upper with mismatched color blocking on each shoe’s collar, heel overlay and signature Swoosh. Additional common details include a white foam midsole and contrasting black rubber outsole. Atop the white nylon tongue, a black woven tag features red Jumpman branding.

results.name: Solefly x Air Jordan 10 Retro Cleat 'Super Bowl' PE
results.story: In honor of the Big Game, the Solefly x Air Jordan 10 Retro Cleat 'Super Bowl' PE was presented to a hand-selected group of top high school recruits from South Florida, all of whom were invited to participate in an exclusive flag football scrimmage. The performance football cleat features an Air Jordan 10 upper, constructed from white leather and mesh with contrasting pops of orange at the mudguard and heel, the latter featuring mismatched Solefly and Jumpman branding.

results.name: Air Jordan 34 PF 'Unite'
results.story: The Air Jordan 34 PF ‘Unite’ shows off an iridescent finish on the eyestay and heel panel, featuring mismatched Nike Air branding between the left and right shoe. The rest of the upper is built with white synthetic leather and translucent textile, supported by a midsole that combines an Eclipse Plate with visible Zoom Air for extra-responsive cushioning. A herringbone-tread rubber outsole delivers superior traction underfoot.

results.name: Air Jordan 34 'Unite'
results.story: The Air Jordan 34 'Iridescent' is designed to shine on the hardwood, thanks to iridescent detailing on the eyestay and heel panel, the latter accented with mismatched multicolor pull loops and Nike Air logo hits. The rest of the all-white upper is constructed from semi-translucent mesh and synthetic, complete with similarly mismatched red and blue Flight branding on each tongue. The mid-top is anchored by a crisp white midsole and an icy translucent rubber midsole.

results.name: Jordan Maxin 200 'Fire Red'
results.story: The Jordan Maxin 200 'Fire Red' showcases a familiar color scheme on a lifestyle silhouette with design cues inspired by the Air Jordan 5. They include a silver reflective tongue and a translucent grill on the quarter panel, both complementing an upper that combines patent leather and full-grain leather. A black foam midsole offsets the all-white finish up top, complete with a visible Max Air unit tinted red.

results.name: Jordan Jumpman 2020 PF 'Infrared 23'
results.story: The Jordan Jumpman 2020 PF 'Infrared 23' highlights a familiar color scheme on a lightweight build, executed with a blend of single-layer black mesh and matching synthetic leather overlays. Contrasting pops of color arrive via red zigzag stitching around the eyestay and metallic silver on the branding elements, including a silver Jumpman logo on the tongue and ‘Flight’ script on the heel. The foam midsole houses a large Zoom Air unit in the forefoot

results.name: Jordan 1 Mid ALT PS 'Noble Red'
results.story: Made for little kids, the Jordan 1 Mid ALT PS 'Noble Red' applies a familiar color scheme to a modified version of the classic silhouette that uses stretch laces and hook-and-loop closure for easy on and off. The upper features a white leather quarter panel with black leather overlays and contrasting pops of Noble Red on the collar, toe box and branding elements. The mid-top rides on a solid white foam midsole for a cushioned ride.

results.name: Jordan Why Not Zer0.3 PF 'Gold'
results.story: The Jordan Why Not Zer0.3 takes on a straightforward colorway that tempers the silhouette’s sharp lines and angles. The mid-top’s dual-layer textile upper is entirely finished in black, with contrast gold stitching throughout and a transparent midfoot strap for a lockdown fit. A white foam midsole, housing an Air Zoom Turbo unit made specifically for Russell Westbrook, sits atop a decoupled rubber outsole modeled after the Air Jordan 28.

results.name: Jordan Jumpman 2020 PF 'Metallic Silver'
results.story: The Jordan Jumpman 2020 PF 'Metallic Silver' uses a simple two-tone finish on a performance basketball shoe that promotes dynamic on-court play through lightweight support. The black textile upper is fortified with leather overlays and midfoot webbing for a lock-down fit. The neutral tones are accented by iridescent detailing that shines at the back of the collar. The midsole packs a Zoom Air unit at the forefoot for responsive cushioning.

results.name: Air Jordan 34 PF 'Chinese New Year'
results.story: The Air Jordan 34 PF ‘Chinese New Year’ rings in the Year of the Rat with a Chinese coin-inspired design on the sneaker’s translucent textile paneling. The rest of the upper, constructed from a blend of leather, synthetic and mesh, maintains a neutral white and black color scheme, with contrasting pops of Digital Pink on the webbing heel tabs. It all rides on a lightweight foam midsole that combines an Eclipse plate with Zoom Air cushioning.

results.name: Jordan Why Not Zer0.3 PF 'Unite'
results.story: The Jordan Why Not Zer0.3 PF ‘Unite’ combines a classic blend of colors with jagged lines and an eclectic mix of materials, both emblematic of Russell Westbrook’s hard-charging style of play. Additional details include a translucent midfoot strap for a lockdown fit and pull tabs at the tongue and heel for easy on and off. An Air Zoom Turbo unit provides responsive cushioning in the midsole, which is reinforced by a split rubber outsole for flexible traction.

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Mid GS 'Triple White'
results.story: Made for big kids, the Air Jordan 1 Mid GS ‘Triple White’ delivers a pristine take on the classic silhouette. The tumbled leather upper is accented with a tonal stitching, perforated detailing on the toe box and a smooth leather Swoosh. A woven tongue tag maintains the all-white aesthetic, along with a debossed Jordan Wings logo on the lateral collar flap. The mid-top silhouette rides on a resilient foam midsole, supported by a rubber outsole underfoot.

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Mid SE TD 'Multicolored Swoosh'
SoleFly x Air Jordan 10 Retro 'Velvet Brown'
results.story: This iteration of the Air Jordan 10 is a retro sneaker that marks another collaboration between SoleFly, a Miami-based sneaker boutique, and Jordan Brand. Released in December 2019 during Art Basel, the shoe is presented with a colorway of Velvet Brown, black, Reflect Silver and Parachute Beige. Like the OG, which debuted in 1994, it features a premium upper, Jordan signature details and an outsole with alternating stripes that represent MJ's career achievements.

results.name: Dover Street Market x CLOT x Air Jordan 1 Mid 'Monochromarket'
results.story: Celebrating the concept store’s 15th anniversary, the Dover Street Market x CLOT x Air Jordan 1 Mid 'Monochromarket' launched exclusively at DSM London on Black Friday 2019. The all-black design features a tearaway nylon upper covered in CLOT’s signature Silk Royale brocade, an in-house pattern that dates back to 2007. Additional details include an embroidered Swoosh and Chinese coin-inspired lace dubrae in an aged copper finish.

results.name: Jordan Why Not Zer0.2 'Flash Crimson'
results.story: Nike celebrates Russell Westbrook's birthday with a special-edition Jordan Why Not Zer0.2. Arrived in November 2019, the sneaker is built with a mesh upper combining leather and translucent film overlays, exposed tongue foam and a deconstructed heel. Flash Crimson icons printed on the pull tabs salute the athlete. The decoupled midsole with Zoom Air cushioning and multidirectional rubber outsole return.

results.name: Jack Daniel's x The Shoe Surgeon x Air Jordan 4 'Cave Spring'
Air Jordan 34 PF 'Eclipse'
results.story: The Nike Air Jordan 34 PF 'Eclipse' extends the iconic line's legacy in a future-forward design merging modern and heritage elements. Debuted in November 2019, this edition has been created with a black translucent and textile upper, 'Flight' branding on the breathable tongue and three pull tabs. An echoed Jumpman graphic graces the heel. Coupled with a herringbone rubber outsole, the sneaker employs an Eclipse plate and Zoom Air tech in the midsole for explosive energy return.

results.name: Jordan 10 Retro PS 'Cool Grey'
results.story: Calling out a decade of All-Star achievements, the Jordan 10 Retro PS 'Cool Grey' mirrors the adult shoe with heritage detail that celebrates a legend. Designed by Tinker Hatfield when Michael Jordan was enjoying 'retirement' on the baseball field, the AJ10 was worn by other NBA players who liked the Dynamic Fit collar and lockdown comfort of its quick-lacing system and striated eyelet straps. Underfoot, Jordan's career accomplishments are printed across the durable rubber outsole.

results.name: Air Jordan 5 Retro PS 'Wolf Grey Hot Lava'
results.story: The Nike Air Jordan 5 Retro PS is modeled after Tinker Hatfield's iconic design, which initially hit the court in 1990. Produced in October 2019, this kid's edition is kitted out in Wolf Grey synthetic nubuck with transparent netting inserts, flecked laces and a Jumpman on the tongue. Its sockliner, '23' embroidery and lace lock are updated in Hot Lava. The sneaker boasts a white midsole with an Air pocket and bright, translucent rubber outsole.

results.name: Jordan Why Not Zer0.2 SE 'Orange Pulse'
results.story: The Jordan Why Not Zer0.2 SE gives Russell Westbrook's signature shoe a lightweight design with a deconstructed upper. Released in October 2019 as Russell prepared for his first season with the Houston Rockets, the sneaker possesses a color scheme of white, black, Particle Grey and Orange Pulse. Jordan and Westbrook branding, including the 2017 NBA MVP's signature 'Why not?' quote, are displayed throughout. A curved heel, translucent midfoot saddle and forefoot Zoom Air finish the style.

results.name: Eminem x Carhartt x Air Jordan 4 'Black Chrome'
results.story: One of Eminem’s most coveted sneaker collaborations, this limited edition ‘Carhartt’ Air Jordan 4 was made exclusively for select family and friends of the Detroit rapper back in 2015, with ten additional pairs auctioned off on Ebay. The design consists of a black Carhartt twill upper, metallic silver lace tabs, a contrasting white midsole, visible Air unit, and a grippy grey outsole. Signature details include Eminem’s backwards “E” logo and a Jason Voorhees mask at the heel.

results.name: Jordan Why Not Zer0.2 SE PF 'Orange Pulse'
results.story: The Nike Jordan Why Not Zer0.2 SE PF is a dynamic basketball sneaker characterizing Russell Westbrook's chaotic game. Unveiled in October 2019, this rendition is emblazoned with the athlete's signature motto across the textile upper and leather lacing panels. Mismatched logos in an Orange Pulse color detail the pull tabs. Underfoot, a Zoom Air-boosted midsole with a midfoot shank and decoupled rubber outsole enhance propulsion and court control.

results.name: Jordan 4 Retro PS 'Loyal Blue'
results.story: The Nike Jordan 4 Retro PS is a weatherized interpretation of the iconic sneaker popularized by Michael Jordan during his 1988-89 season. Emerged in October 2019, this kid's iteration repels water thanks to a Loyal Blue leather upper with an insulating two-tone sockliner, perforated underlays and lace wings. A Jumpman graces the heel and 'Flight' branding details the tongue. A two-tone midsole with Air cushioning rests atop a rubber outsole.

results.name: Jordan 4 Retro TD 'Loyal Blue'
results.story: The Nike Jordan 4 Retro TD winterizes the cultural icon, which rose to prominence on the court after Michael Jordan's 1988-89 season. Arrived in October 2019, this kid's version offers warmth and protection in waterproof Loyal Blue leather with a plush two-tone sockliner, perforated inserts and lace wings. 'Flight' branding remains on tongue and a Jumpman dons the heel. The sneaker has a bicolor Air-imbued midsole and rubber outsole.

results.name: Air Jordan 34 PF 'Bred'
results.story: The Nike Air Jordan 34 PF continues the legendary line's legacy in a modern, tech-forward silhouette. Unveiled in September 2019, this edition boasts a textile and translucent upper with reflective laces, perforated accents and three pull tabs. The lauded Bred color scheme is expressed through the nubuck trim and custom branding. A Zoom Air-equipped midsole toting a stabilizing Eclipse plate and herringbone rubber outsole offer a responsive feel and traction.

results.name: Jordan Flight Luxe 'Thunder Blue'
results.story: The Nike Air Jordan Flight Luxe blends hoops DNA inspired by the Air Jordan 15 with hybrid versatility. Debuted in September 2019, this edition is given a Thunder Blue ribbed mesh upper tooled with a Flywire lacing system, branded tongue pull and reinforced toe. An iconic wordmark is debossed on the leather heel counter. The sneaker's molded one-piece sole unit comes with a geometric tread pattern granting traction and durability.

results.name: Jordan Proto React Z 'Anthracite'
results.story: The Nike Air Jordan Proto React Z takes its unconventional styling and technical design from space suits. Introduced in September 2019, this version is brought together in a black aeronautics-inspired shroud encasing a supportive bootie, a hook-and-loop heel strap and reinforcing TPU overlays. Anthracite branding is placed throughout. The sneaker carries a matching cushioned midsole and rubber outsole with deep tread.

results.name: Jordan Proto React Z 'Bright Crimson'
results.story: The Nike Air Jordan Proto React Z reflects inspiration drawn from space suits in its unconventional design. Unveiled in September 2019, this iteration makes use of a Bright Crimson inner bootie wrapped in a white aeronautics-inspired shroud, a hook-and-loop heel strap and TPU accents. Logos detail the zipper tape and tongue. The sneaker rests on top of a cushioned midsole and two-tone rubber outsole with an intricate tread pattern.

results.name: Jordan Jumpman 2020 PF 'Black'
results.story: Taking after the AJ34, the Nike Air Jordan Jumpman 2020 PF brings a sense of security and response to the hardwood. This variant—updated in September 2019—is constructed of mesh reinforced by black leather overlays, midfoot stability webbing and a TPU toe cap. Contrast Jumpman emblems are seen throughout and Flight branding is written on heel. The sneaker is provided with a Zoom Air-cushioned midsole and herringbone rubber outsole with a pop of neon.

results.name: Jordan Jumpman 2020 PF 'Aurora Green'
results.story: The Jordan Jumpman 2020 PF 'Aurora Green' is primarily white with a leather upper. The Jumpman logo appears on the middle panel in mint-like Aurora Green, matching the color of the tongue and sole. This Air Jordan basketball shoe released in September 2019 and features a white netting that stretches from the middle panel to the toe box, layering over black and white stripes. The word ‘Flight’ on the heel panel salutes Jordan’s basketball prowess.

results.name: Wmns Air Jordan 1 Nova XX 'Black Sail'
Air Jordan 12 Retro TD 'Cool Grey'
results.story: The Nike Air Jordan 12 Retro TD is a throwback to the sneaker Michael Jordan wore during his famed "Flu Game" against the Utah Jazz in 1997. Launched in September 2019, this kid's version shows off a stitched leather upper detailed with an asymmetrical Cool Grey panel and rope laces. Color-pop Jumpman logos embellish the tongue and run down the heel. A cushioned midsole and supportive rubber outsole round out the design.

results.name: Air Jordan 34 'Blue Void'
results.story: The Air Jordan 34 'Blue Void' was one of two OG colorways released September 25th, 2019 to mark the unveiling of the Jordan game shoe. Carrying on the Jordan legacy was NBA rookie Zion Williamson, whose aerial play and vertical approach to the game were mirrored by the shoe's stripped-down construction and explosive design. This includes two Zoom Air units in the midsole connected by the firm yet lightweight and flexible Eclipse plate.

results.name: Jordan Jumpman 2020 PF 'Platinum Tint'
results.story: The Jordan Jumpman 2020 is a lightweight basketball sneaker inspired by the Air Jordan 34. Released in September 2019, the shoe features a performance mesh upper, structured overlays and midfoot webbing. Dressed in black, Platinum Tint and Summit White, the sneaker prominently displays Jumpman and Flight branding. Completing the model is a Zoom Air unit to promote responsive cushioning and a herringbone tread pattern on the outsole to help with traction.

results.name: Wmns Air Jordan 1 Mid 'White Ivory'
results.story: The Nike Wmns Air Jordan 1 Mid is based on the original mid-80s design conceptualized by Peter Moore. Launched in September 2019, this women's edition refreshes the iconic template for the style conscious in white leather with ivory defining the Swooshes, lace closure and tongue label. Wings branding is kept on the collar. An Air-cushioned rubber cupsole brings the sneaker's court style full circle.

results.name: Air Jordan 3 Retro 'Solefly'
results.story: Nike teamed up with Miami sneaker boutique SoleFly on a super-limited edition Air Jordan 3 Retro that is unreleased and only given out to Friends and Family. The sneaker shows off a white tumbled leather replete with iconic elephant-print panels and contrast mudguard. Bright accents and color-pop Jumpman embroidery are inspired by the Florida Lottery. Hidden behind the back pull tab is '305' and a graphic of the state of Florida.

results.name: Jordan Why Not Zer0.2 SE PF 'Black Vast Grey'
results.story: This iteration of the Jordan Why Not Zer0.2 presents Russell Westbrook's signature sneaker with a colorway of black, Vast Grey, white, Sail and Metallic Gold. The lightweight shoe features a deconstructed upper, Jumpman and Westbrook branding, a translucent midfoot saddle and a curved heel. A heel pull tab promotes easy on and off, while forefoot Zoom Air and a cored-out traction pattern on the outsole combine to provide a cushioned, secure fit.

results.name: Jordan Why Not Zer0.2 SE PF 'City Tour'
results.story: Debuted in September 2019, the Jordan Why Not Zer0.2 SE PF 'City Tour' updates the Westbrook signature shoe with summer hoops in mind. This special edition is lightweight and boasts a mixed-material upper with a translucent midfoot saddle, exposed foam detailing and visible Flywire cables. A barcode is printed on the heel tab. Its Zoom Air midsole and rubber outsole with a cored-out traction pattern offers lightweight cushioning and flexibility.

results.name: Jordan 11 Retro Little Flex TD 'Starfish'
results.story: The Jordan 11 Retro Little Flex TD 'Starfish' is a kids' shoe that draws inspiration from the iconic Air Jordan 11, a model that debuted in 1995. This version released in September 2019 with a lightweight fabric upper, Jumpman branding and the AJ11's signature shiny patent leather mudguard. Dressed in Sail, Starfish and black, the sneaker offers a slip-on design with a heel pull tab for easy on and off, plus a soft foam midsole to promote a cushioned fit.

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Mid ALT PS 'What The'
results.story: The Jordan 1 Mid ALT PS 'What The' presents an updated take on Michael Jordan's first signature sneaker with a unique colorway. Released in September 2019, the mid-cut kids' shoe features a black premium upper that displays the Nike Swoosh in Total Orange. Jumpman branding is displayed on the tongue and the Wings logo appears near the ankle, while a heel pull tab promotes easy on and off. Various pastel-like colors provide accents with a white midsole and outsole finishing the look.

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Mid ALT TD 'Triple White'
results.story: An all-white colorway graces this edition of the iconic Air Jordan 1. The mid-cut kids' shoe, which released in September 2019, is an updated take on Michael Jordan's first signature sneaker that debuted in 1985. It features a leather and synthetic upper, a padded collar, a heel pull tab, and Jumpman and Nike branding. A hook-and-loop closure is in place over the sneaker's stretch laces to promote easy on and off, while a foam midsole helps deliver a cushioned fit.

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Mid ALT TD 'What The'
results.story: The Jordan 1 Mid ALT TD 'What The' is a modernized take on the Air Jordan 1 that debuted in April 1985. The kids' shoe released in September 2019 with a black leather and synthetic upper that displays the Nike Swoosh in Total Orange. Jumpman branding resides on the tongue and the classic Wings logo appears on the collar, while a heel pull tab, stretch laces and a hook-and-loop closure make the sneaker easier to put on and take off. A contrasting white midsole and outsole finish the style.

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Mid ALT PS 'Triple White'
results.story: The Jordan 1 Mid ALT PS 'Triple White' offers an updated take on Michael Jordan's iconic debut signature sneaker with a monochromatic style. Released in September 2019, the all-white kids' shoe features several elements from the 1985 original model, including a premium upper, Jordan and Nike branding, and a perforated toe box. This version also comes with a heel pull tab and a lace overlay with an integrated Velcro closure system. Finishing the look is a white rubber outsole.

results.name: Jordan Jumpman Diamond Low PF 'White Silver'
results.story: The Nike Jordan Jumpman Diamond Low PF is a progressive basketball sneaker providing stability and responsiveness to run the court. Launched in August 2019, this edition features a white textile upper encased in a silver cage system, designed by Tinker Hatfield, for lightweight security. A metallic Jumpman takes shape on the lateral and a label is stitched to the tongue. Its Zoom Air midsole and rubber outsole optimize energy return and traction.

results.name: Air Jordan 33 SE 'FIBA'
results.story: Primed for international competition, the Air Jordan 33 SE 'FIBA' combines advanced hoops technology with a distinctly international vibe. Jumpman branding on the tongue and a midfoot FastFit system are seen in gold to capture the goal of every global competitor, while Chinese characters spell “Love The Game” on the tongue's interior. The shoe released August 23, 2019 in anticipation of the FIBA World Cup held in China.

results.name: Jordan Jumpman Diamond Mid PF 'Hyper Violet'
results.story: The Jordan Jumpman Diamond Mid PF 'Hyper Violet' is a performance basketball shoe designed by the legendary Tinker Hatfield. Released in August 2019, the sneaker comes with a white perforated mesh upper and Hyper Royal accents on the Jumpman branding, heel pull tab and part of the midsole. Hyper Violet covers a plastic webbing overlay that extends up from the midsole, while a white rubber outsole features a multidirectional pattern and the text "Jordan Performance By Tinker Hatfield."

results.name: Jordan 1 Mid SE TD 'Black Field Purple'
Air Jordan 1 Mid TD 'Multi-Color'
results.story: The Nike Air Jordan 1 Mid TD gives little ones a piece of nostalgia with hoops-inspired functionality and storytelling elements. Produced in August 2019, this kid's variant in a vibrant multi-color palette alternates between leather and nubuck for a 90s retro aesthetic. Wings insignia is debossed into the collar, Flight branding is found on the tongue and bright Swooshes grace the sides. A duo-tone rubber cupsole helps build mobility.

results.name: Travis Scott x Air Jordan 1 Low 'Mocha' Sample
Jordan CP3.XII 'Multi-Color'
results.story: This iteration of the Jordan CP3.XII is presented with a multi-color makeup and lightweight Flyknit construction. Released in July 2019, it's the twelfth signature shoe for perennial NBA All-Star point guard Chris Paul. Among its highlights are tongue and heel pull tabs, an adjustable lacing system and a side wrap, which collectively promote a comfortable, secure fit. CP3 and Jordan branding, a Zoom Air unit and multidirectional traction pattern on the outsole round out the style.

results.name: Jordan Why Not Zer0.2 SE PF 'Red Orbit'
results.story: This version of Russell Westbrook's second signature shoe, the Jordan Why Not Zer0.2 SE PF 'Red Orbit,' features a deconstructed upper strong enough to keep up with Westbrook's playing style. Released in July 2019, the sneaker's bold design includes Red Orbit, black and white with Jordan and Westbrook branding highlighted throughout. The performance-based sneaker also comes with Zoom Air in the forefoot, a curved heel and a rubber outsole with a specialized traction pattern.

results.name: Travis Scott x Air Jordan 4 Retro 'Purple Suede - White Midsole'
results.story: Unreleased to the public and only available as a friends-and-family exclusive in July 2019, the Travis Scott x Nike Air Jordan 4 Retro 'Purple Suede - White Midsole' was worn by the Houston rapper at several different events through the year. The sneaker is dressed in purple suede with black grid mesh, matte lace wings and semi-transparent eyestays. Scott's name can be found under the left tongue and a Cactus Jack logo in red graces the right heel. Visible Air tech and translucent outsole rubber outsole finalize the design.

results.name: Jordan Proto React 'Barley Volt'
results.story: The Air Jordan Proto React is inspired by the design of a space suit, evolving the iconic brand's concept of flight. Unveiled in July 2019, this 'Barely Volt' iteration is created with a semi-translucent shroud, a sock-like internal bootie and a reflective tongue detail. Dynamic lacing and a hook-and-loop heel strap customize the fit. Its contrast rubber sole features an exaggerated herringbone tread pattern for enhanced traction.

results.name: Jordan 6 Rings PS 'Dark Concord'
results.story: Issued in July 2019, the Nike Air Jordan 6 Rings sneaker combines elements from each shoe that Michael Jordan wore en route to his six championships. This kid's variant sports a white mesh upper with matching leather accents, branded lace straps and a black perforated patent mudguard. Jumpman branding in Dark Concord details the tongue. A Zoom Air unit within the midsole and a rubber outsole work together to grant responsive stability.

results.name: Air Jordan 33 SE PF 'Cement Grey'
results.story: The Air Jordan 33 SE PF continues the brand's legacy of innovation and high-performance design for a next-generation concept of flight. Unveiled in July 2019, this 'Cement Grey' version rewrites the template using a neoprene inner bootie, a bicolor textile overlay and tumbled leather panels. Neon detailing brightens up the FastFit closure system. A responsive Zoom Air and FlightSpeed midsole layers an icy translucent rubber outsole.

results.name: Jordan Hydro 7 V2 GS 'Black Gym Red'
results.story: The Jordan Hydro 7 V2 GS 'Black Gym Red' is a kids' slide that displays the famous Jumpman logo in Gym Red on an adjustable midfoot strap. Released in July 2019, the strap also features the brand's popular elephant print, which debuted on 1988's Air Jordan 3. A soft foam midsole promotes a comfortable, cushioned fit, while a durable white rubber outsole helps deliver traction.

results.name: Jordan Why Not Zer0.1 Low PFX 'Monsoon Blue'
results.story: The Jordan Why Not Zer0.1 Low PFX 'Monsoon Blue' is a low-top, two-tone version of Russell Westbrook's first signature sneaker. Dressed in Monsoon Blue and Midnight Navy, the shoe was designed to capture the unique style on and off the court of Westbrook, who was named the NBA's Most Valuable Player in 2017. Released in July 2019, it features Jordan and Westbrook branding, a mesh upper and a full-length Zoom Air unit.

results.name: Jordan Trunner LT
results.story: The Jordan Trunner LT was designed specifically to aid athletes through conditioning and speed drills for team sports. Emerged in June 2019, this edition boasts a breathable white mesh upper replete with a supportive internal structure and film eyestays. Bold branding is printed on the tongue and a Jumpman graces the lateral. A color-pop React midsole wrapped in a contrast latticework cage and rubber outsole match energy return and grip.

results.name: Jordan CP3.XII 'Unfinished Business'
results.story: This take on the Jordan CP3.XII, released in July 2019, offers an 'Unfinished Business' color scheme dominated by black and University Red. It features Chris Paul branding—including the tongue's Metallic Gold owl logo, a nod to CP3's wisdom—and the iconic Jumpman on the toe box and heel. Highlights of the sneaker include its lightweight performance knit upper, leather quarter panel and Zoom Air. A white midsole provides contrast and a multidirectional traction pattern finishes the look.

results.name: Jordan CP3.XII 'Dr. Jekyll and Mr. Hyde'
results.story: The Jordan CP3.XII 'Dr. Jekyll and Mr. Hyde' presents NBA star point guard Chris Paul's twelfth signature sneaker in a colorway of black, white, Vivid Purple and Metallic Gold. Released in July 2019, it features a performance knit upper with a leather quarter panel and forefoot lacing system. The sneaker displays CP3 and Jordan branding, while a heel pull tab promotes easy on and off. Zoom Air resides in the forefoot and an outsole with a herringbone traction pattern completes the model.

results.name: Jordan Trunner LT
results.story: The Jordan Trunner LT supplements conditioning and speed training for athletes who play team sports. Debuted in June 2019, this version has a breathable white mesh upper featuring an internal structure for support and two-tone laces. A bright logo graces the tongue and Jumpman branding is found on the lateral side. A matching React midsole with a black latticework cage and rubber outsole bring response and stability.

results.name: Jordan Trunner LT 'Black'
results.story: The Jordan Trunner LT 'Black' is a training sneaker that prioritizes comfort, style and performance. Released in July 2019, black dominates the shoe's colorway, with Particle Grey, white and Gym Red also making an appearance. It comes with a low-cut silhouette, lightweight mesh upper and Jumpman branding on the quarter panel. A caged overlay near the heel helps with stability, while Nike React technology promotes lightweight cushioning.

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Low 'Black Gold'
results.story: The Air Jordan 1 Low 'Black Gold' is an updated take on the icon that first appeared in 1985. This low-top version, released in June 2019, is dominated by black, which coats the leather upper, its nubuck overlays and the Wings branding on the heel. The tongue's Jumpman logo and Nike Swooshes on both sides of the shoe appear in gold. Several elements from the OG model are present, including the toe box perforations and pivot point tread pattern on the outsole.

results.name: Air Jordan Fusion 12 'Obsidian'
results.story: The Nike Air Jordan Fusion 12 fuses distinctive elements of two iconic sneakers, the Air Force 1 and the Air Jordan 12. Unveiled in June 2019, this version's Obsidian tumbled leather upper has been detailed with 'Rising Sun' stitch work, matching Swooshes and a signature ankle strap. While Jumpman branding pops on the tongue and heel pull, the white toe cap and laces add further contrast. Its midsole, with an Air unit, gets a split-colored finish.

results.name: Jordan 3 Retro Bp 'Wolf Grey'
results.story: The Nike Air Jordan 3 Retro Bp nods to Michael Jordan’s second slam dunk contest win with heritage elements modernized for young hoops enthusiasts. Unveiled in June 2019, this kid's edition holds a Wolf Grey tumbled leather upper featuring a smooth mudguard, TPU lace eyelets and a perforated collar. Metallic silver highlights the elephant-print panels and Jumpman branding. The sneaker has a cushioned midsole and rubber outsole.

results.name: Jordan Why Not Zer0.2 'Cotton Shot'
results.story: A refreshed take on NBA player Russell Westbrook’s signature silhouette, the Nike Jordan Why Not Zer0.2 sneaker is updated with this 'Cotton Shot' rendition. Released in June 2019, this version is inspired by childhood workouts with Westbrook’s father who used to call Russell's buckets ‘cotton shots.’ A Washed Coral hue dominates the design, with mesh and leather making up the supportive upper. The shoe is underscored by a sculpted sole and gum rubber tread.

results.name: Wmns Jordan Air Latitude 720
results.story: A work of modern technology and reverence for heritage, the Wmns Jordan Air Latitude 720 blends the personalities of the Flight Utility ethos and the Air Jordan 8. This women's version—launched in June 2019—encases its mesh bootie in a synthetic cage. Speed lacing and a hook and loop closure issue dual fit customization. More than 70% of recycled materials power the 720 Max Air unit. A court-inspired tread pattern is assigned to the rubber outsole.

results.name: Air Jordan 3 Retro 'Oregon Pit Crew'
results.story: Nike released a colorway of the classic Air Jordan 3 silhouette in celebration of the University of Oregon student cheer section known as the Pit Crew. The Air Jordan 3 Retro 'Oregon Pit Crew' features a black leather upper with iconic elephant print designs on the mudguard and heel. The low top also boasts grey accents around the collar, tongue, and on the eyestay, as well as an Oregon “O” logo on the tongue, a duck foot motif on the heel, and a partially encapsulated Air unit for responsive cushioning.

results.name: Wmns Jordan Air Latitude 720
results.story: With respect for its iconic heritage, the Wmns Jordan Air Latitude 720 takes cues from the Air Jordan 8 and Flight Utility ethos in terms of innovation and futuristic aesthetic. This women's edition—unveiled in June 2019—presents a mesh bootie with crossover synthetic caging, a dual closure system and a deconstructed textile collar. The 720 Max Air unit and sculpted outsole tread pattern finalize the avant-garde profile.

results.name: Jordan Hydro 7 V2 ''
results.story: The Air Jordan Hydro 7 V2 takes inspiration from different Jordan Brand silhouettes, readapting its iconic look for post-workout recovery. Issued in June 2019, this update features an adjustable midfoot strap detailed with the archival elephant print and a metallic Jumpman emblem. A Solarsoft foam footbed grants a cushy underfoot. Enhanced with Air technology, the single-piece sole is chiseled with segmented, concentric grooves for flexibility and grip.

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Low ALT TD 'Ember Glow'
results.story: The Jordan 1 Low ALT TD 'Ember Glow' is a kids' shoe featuring elements of an iconic silhouette first seen in 1985. This version, released in June 2019, is highlighted by Jordan branding on the tongue and heel, flexible bands on the foot and an upper constructed of leather and synthetic leather. White covers most of the shoe, contrasted with Ember Glow, Barely Volt and black. A foam midsole and the AJ1's pivot point tread pattern on the outsole finish the look.

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Low ALT PS 'Ember Glow'
results.story: Released in June 2019, the Jordan 1 Low ALT PS 'Ember Glow' offers an updated design on Michael Jordan's first signature sneaker. This low-top version comes in kids' sizes with a color scheme of white, Ember Glow, Barely Volt and black. Bands with Velcro closures make the sneaker easy to put on and take off. Jordan signature branding and the famous Nike Swoosh are featured on the leather and synthetic leather upper, while white foam cushioning finishes the look.

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Retro High SB 'NYC to Paris' Sample
Air Jordan 16 Retro 'Veteran's Day' Sample
results.story: First seen in May 2019, the Nike Air Jordan 16 Retro 'Veteran's Day' commemorates the holiday as part of a five-piece pack. The unreleased player exclusive sneaker features an Olive nubuck upper, woven detailing and a detachable lace cover revealing a camouflage print. Branding is kept to a minimum with a metal Jumpman emblem and logos down the heel. The midsole's visible blow-molded Air component and a transparent rubber outsole supply court-inspired support.

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Retro High SB 'LA to Chicago' Sample
Trophy Room x Air Jordan 5 Retro 'Ice Blue'
results.story: The Trophy Room x Air Jordan 5 Retro sneaker draws inspiration from the real-life trophy room in the Jordan family home. This 'Ice Blue' rendition is replete with a rich suede upper, hits of University Red, Sail and a metallic gold lace lock. Each lateral heel is embroidered with metallic gold numerals—'23' and '5'—the jersey numbers worn by MJ and his son, Marcus. Below, the sneaker's translucent rubber sole displays a wood-grain motif to reference the court-style flooring in MJ's trophy room. A total of 7,000 pairs were released in May 2019, each individually numbered.

results.name: Trophy Room x Air Jordan 5 Retro 'Friends & Family'
results.story: The Trophy Room x Air Jordan 5 Retro 'Friends & Family' was given out to a select few in May 2019 and limited to 223 pairs. Steeped in commemorative detail, the shoe was inspired by the real-life trophy room in Michael Jordan's family home. Its upper is crafted from premium suede in striking University Red, complemented by hits of Ice Blue and Sail. The numerals '23' and '5' are embroidered at the heels, signifying the jersey numbers of Michael Jordan and his son, Marcus. A translucent sole seals in a wood grain pattern, similar to the court-style flooring in Jordan's trophy room.

results.name: Travis Scott x Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG 'Mocha' Sample
Wmns Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG 'Twist' Oneness Special Box
Travis Scott x Air Jordan 4 Retro 'Cactus Jack' Friends & Family
Wmns Air Jordan 1 Jester XX Low 'White'
results.story: Released in April 2019, the Wmns Air Jordan 1 Jester XX Low 'White' offers an updated take on a classic silhouette that debuted in 1985. This version, a women's shoe, comes with leather in the upper and a dual-zip closure integrated into its laceless design. The iconic Wings logo graces the tongue and heel with the Nike Swoosh adorning the side panel. Nike Air promotes responsive cushioning and a rubber outsole with a pivot point tread pattern rounds out the style.

results.name: Air Jordan 33 PF 'Metallic Gold'
results.story: The Air Jordan 33 PF 'Metallic Gold' applies modern technology to a classic hoops brand with flight as its central theme. Released in April 2019 with a colorway of black, Metallic Gold and white, the sneaker possesses a lightweight textile upper with a camouflage design, leather and synthetic overlays, and pull tabs on the tongue and heel. Its FastFit system promotes a speedy, secure fit, while FlightSpeed technology and Nike Zoom Air help deliver a stable, cushioned feel.

results.name: Jordan Why Not Zer0.2 PF 'Vast Grey'
Jordan Why Not Zer0.2 PF 'Tiger Camo'
results.story: The Air Jordan Why Not Zer0.2 PF takes storytelling to the next level with an eccentric design evocative of Russell Westbrook's personal style and on-court game. Updated in April 2019, this 'Tiger Camo' option incorporates jacquard, camo textile and synthetic skin on the upper. Mismatched eyestays accent the midfoot strap, with the heels inverting the hues. Westbrook’s family crest is featured on the tongue. An exposed midfoot plate and decoupled Zoom sole are designed for explosive play.

results.name: Jordan Why Not Zer0.2 'Triple White'
results.story: The Air Jordan Why Not Zer0.2 captures Russell Westbrook's calculated chaos on the court in a dynamic look imbued with cutting-edge tech. Issued in April 2019, this 'Triple White' version reprises the mixed-textile upper for optimal support and breathability. A midfoot strap and traditional lacing provide stability. Forefoot Zoom Air cushioning and a rubber outsole with aggressive tread facilitate explosive play.

results.name: Air Jordan 3 Retro 'Tinker - Oregon Ducks' PE
results.story: The Air Jordan 3 Retro 'Tinker - Oregon Ducks' PE presents an updated take on a silhouette first seen in 1988. Created by Tinker Hatfield for the University of Oregon's football team and distributed in March 2019 to players, staff and alumni only, the sneaker features a green suede upper and removable Nike Swoosh patches in black, yellow, green and silver. Jumpman branding is displayed on the tongue, while an 'O' adorns the heel. Rounding out the unique look is the brand's popular elephant print and a visible Air-Sole unit.

results.name: Eminem x Air Jordan 4 Retro 'Encore' 2017
results.story: This is the 2017 edition of the Eminem x Air Jordan 4 Retro ‘Encore.’ The shoe is a retro of the original collaboration from 2005, which was distributed to friends and family in celebration of the rapper’s fifth studio album. Featuring a blue nubuck upper with black and grey accents, the shoe was limited to just 23 pairs. Special details include an ‘Eminem’ tag on the interior tongue and ‘Encore’ embroidered on the inside of the heel tab.

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Low ALT PS 'White'
results.story: This low-top version of Nike’s timeless 1985 AJ1 pulls design elements from the original and repackages them into a kid-friendly fit and style. The Jordan 1 Low ALT PS 'White' sneaker features an all-white colorway, from the upper to the outsole. Outfitted in synthetic and genuine leather, the shoe replaces traditional laces with elastic straps and Velcro closures at each side. Soft foam provides cushioning for growing feet.

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Mid BG 'Triple White'
results.story: With a neutral canvas and no color added, the Air Jordan 1 Mid BG 'Triple White' was released March 2019 in spring-inspired minimalism. Designed for grade school kids, this retro hoops sneaker emulates the 1985 Peter Moore adult original with support overlays at the heel, collar, midfoot and mudguard. To address MJ's dynamic play, the shoe was made with a perforated toe box to avoid overheating and sticky rubber traction for sudden starts, stops and cuts.

results.name: Jordan Why Not Zer0.2 PF 'OKC Home'
results.story: This version of the Jordan Why Not Zer0.2 released in February 2019 with a color scheme inspired by Russell Westbrook's former team, the Oklahoma City Thunder. Dressed in white, Total Crimson and Blue Lagoon, the sneaker comes with a deconstructed upper, exposed stitching and a variety of Jordan and Westbrook branding. Designed for performance on the hardwood, it also features a cushioned double-layer heel, a lofted midfoot strap, Zoom Air and a two-piece outsole.

results.name: The Shoe Surgeon x Air Jordan 1 High 'Golden State Warriors'
results.story: The Shoe Surgeon, Dominic Chambrone, designed six customized Nike Air Jordan 1s to celebrate the Golden State Warriors' 2019 championship season. Raffled off in March 2019, the Shoe Surgeon x Air Jordan 1 High 'Golden State Warriors' sneaker is dressed in patent leather, wrapped in Flywire. Decked out in jerseys and nets used during the Warriors' final run, the exclusive sneaker is finished with a debossed ‘Strength in Numbers’ logo and team branding.

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Retro High 'All Star - White' 2019
Jordan Why Not Zer0.2 'All Star'
results.story: The Jordan Why Not Zer0.2 'All Star' reflects the boldness of Russel Westbrook, NBA superstar, with a multicolored, multi-patterned version of his signature shoe. The upper boasts two types of camo print on its mesh base, while elephant print takes over the toe. The look converges with a primary color scheme on the midfoot strap, midsole, and outsole. A rear panel flap gives a nod to the star's eight All-Star Game appearances.

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Retro High 'All Star - Black' 2019
results.story: In concert with a white model, the Air Jordan 1 Retro High 'All Star - Black' 2019 pays homage to a couple special events with a 300-pair limited run. The sneaker was made available February 17th, 2019—Jordan's 56th birthday—to mark the NBA All-Star game being played in Charlotte. Imagined by the Jumpman himself, this version of Tinker Hatfield's 1985 classic has a quilted-leather upper and tongue tag from the 1991 game. Proceeds of original sales went to the Charlotte Hornets Foundation.

results.name: Jordan Why Not Zer0.2 PF 'The Family'
results.story: Russell Westbrook is known for his commitment to those closest to him, and the kids’-sized version of his signature Jordan Why Not Zer0.2 PF ‘The Family’ shows the love with special details. The black and white color pays tribute to Westbrook’s parents, who he says were there before the bright lights, and an exposed tag features “The Family” written in gold. Aside from the tributes, the upper also features varied textures and a cutout in the outsole, reflecting Westbrook’s eye-catching style.

results.name: Air Jordan 33 'Chinese New Year'
results.story: The Air Jordan 33 ‘Chinese New Year’ rings in the lunar new year with a celebratory design that features a black mesh upper accented with pops of red and metallic gold throughout. Both the tongue and sockliner are printed with a traditional Chinese patchwork design known as Bai Jia Yi, while patent leather overlays appear in matching black. A FlightSpeed plate and Zoom Air support the shoe underfoot.

results.name: Air Jordan 33 PF 'Chinese New Year'
results.story: Released in February of 2018, the Nike Air Jordan 33 PF 'Chinese New Year' sneaker has a mesh upper with firework and flower print on the ankle overlays, a reference to Chinese New Year celebrations. The red, black and white colorway seen here has become the go-to for Nike’s CNY creations, and the festive touches continue with Chinese lettering “2018” script on the inner tongue. A two-tone midsole-outsole featuring a Jumpman logo tops off the look.

results.name: Air Jordan 33 PF 'All-Star'
results.story: The Air Jordan 33 PF 'All-Star' was released in January 2019, just a few weeks ahead of All-Star Weekend. This take on the Air Jordan 33 features a mesh construction with Metallic Silver overlays for shine and support. The shoe incorporates a FastFit system in place of laces, allowing for easy entry, tightening and release. The 'All-Star' shoe displays a cosmic-inspired graphic laid below a clear, micro-treaded sole.

results.name: Jordan Why Not Zer0.2 'Future History'
results.story: The Jordan Why Not Zer0.2 'Future History' sneaker honors Russell Westbrook's basketball career in his signature sneaker released in January 2019. The upper is comprised of mesh and lofted materials featuring personal touches like a family crest on the tongue and a colorway highlighting the various uniforms worn by the athlete since starting his sports career in high school. The two-piece Sail White sole is contrasted by a Total Crimson heel with a Jumpman and visible TPU shank.

Air Jordan 1 Mid SE GS 'Deep Royal'
results.story: The Air Jordan 1 is regarded as one of the leading silhouettes in Michael Jordan's signature line. Championed on and off the court, this Air Jordan 1 Mid SE GS 'Deep Royal' kids' sneaker sports a tumbled leather upper with a padded tongue, neoprene collar and a bold lacing system. Signature trademarks and an iconic Wings logo take their usual positions, while pivot point traction on the outsole supports dynamic performance.

results.name: Jordan Jumpman Z 'White'
results.story: Take the iconic Air Jordan 14 silhouette, add a zipper along the upper and discover the futuristic Jordan Jumpman Z 'White' revealed in November 2018. Tinker Hatfield developed the AJ14 in 1998, paying homage to one of the game's most legendary players and his history-making 'last shot' to defeat the Utah Jazz, leading Michael Jordan to his sixth and final NBA championship. The Jumpman Z reflects the original nostalgia-invoking AJ14 silhouette while adding contemporary style and flair.

Jordan Flight Flex Trainer 2 BG 'Neon Orange'
Air Jordan 5 Retro Low PS 'Fire Red'
results.story: The kids'-sized Air Jordan 5 Retro Low GS 'Fire Red' brings back a 1990 classic in sizes made for smaller feet. The low-top upper comes in premium white leather, with red hits on the liner and Jumpman, while black mesh features prominently on the middle panel cutout. Below, a black and red midsole boasts the AJ5's well-known shark's teeth, underscored by a rubber outsole for traction.

results.name: Jordan Hydro 7 Slide 'Varsity Red'
results.story: The Jordan Hydro 7 Slide ‘Varsity Red’ blends comfort and style with its futuristic silhouette and shiny red strap decorated with subtle Jordan branding. The plush sandal features a soft cushioned footbed with a plush feel, and a Solarsoft foam midsole with extra cushion that provides lightweight support, true to Jordan brand form. An adjustable strap lies across the midfoot, offering a snug, personalized fit.

results.name: Jordan Legacy 312 GS 'Black Fire Red'
results.story: The Jordan Legacy 312 GS 'Black Fire Red' is a kids' shoe that mixes classic elements from the Air Jordan 1, Air Jordan 3 and Nike Air Alpha Force. Released in December 2018 and designed by Don C, the high-top sneaker comes with a leather upper, midfoot strap and a visible Air-Sole unit in the heel. It features the Nike Swoosh on the quarter panel, Jumpman branding on the heel and the Jordan Brand's iconic elephant print. A white foam midsole and grey rubber outsole finish the look.

results.name: Jordan Flight Time 14.5 'South Beach'
results.story: Carrying elements and inspirations both rustic and modern, the Jordan Flight Time 14.5 'South Beach' is an example of contrasts that work together. Building on the AJ14 aesthetic, the shoe boasts a look both contemporary and classic: an asymmetrical collar is treated with timeless argyle quilting, while the detached heel stand out with laser-cut geometric patterns. Decked out in a pink-and-turquoise colorway, this pair pays tribute to the life and color of Miami, Florida.

results.name: Jordan Westbrook 0
results.story: This iteration of the Jordan Westbrook 0 released in 2015 with a leather and synthetic upper in white and Metallic Gold accents. Russell Westbrook's first signature lifestyle sneaker draws inspiration from the Air Jordan 11 and comes with Jordan and Westbrook branding, including lace jewels that display the words 'WHY' and 'NOT?' The high-cut shoe has a ghillie lacing system, a reptilian-like pattern on the toe and a vulcanized, smooth rubber outsole.

results.name: Jordan True Flight PS 'Black Gym Red'
Jordan CP3.VII
results.story: The Jordan CP3.VII gives Chris Paul's seventh signature sneaker a color scheme of black, Sprint Red, Chambray Blue and Game Royal. Released in December 2018, it comes with a leather and synthetic upper with perforations for ventilation. Paul branding resides on the tongue, while the iconic Jumpman is displayed on the heel counter. Dynamic Flywire, Nike Zoom and low-profile Podulite promote a secure and cushioned fit, while the outsole helps deliver multidirectional traction.

results.name: Jordan Hydro 11 'Emerald'
results.story: The Air Jordan Hydro 11 'Emerald' sandal blends the comfort and ease of a slide with the bold design of the iconic Air Jordan 11. An adjustable midfoot strap allows a customized fit, decorated with a sleek Jumpman logo and ‘23’ branding to pay homage to Michael Jordan. The sandal is completed with the recognizable Air Jordan 11 patent leather rand and flex grooves on the outsole.

Jordan True Flight BP 'Black Royal Blue Green'
Air Jordan Future BG 'Black'
results.story: The Air Jordan Future BG 'Black' is a kids' shoe with a black woven textile upper. Released in December 2018, the lifestyle sneaker is presented with Jumpman branding in Metallic Gold on its padded tongue and a partially hidden set of asymmetrical laces that twist towards the inside of the foot. A contrasting white foam midsole with Nike Air cushioning sits atop a speckled translucent outsole designed to provide traction on a variety of surfaces.

Jordan J23 'Gym Red'
results.story: The Air Jordan J23 absorbs contemporary elements into a court-inspired profile. Debuted in October 2016, breathable mesh shapes the upper of this 'Gym Red' option with a cushy neoprene collar, a tonal croc-embossed midfoot strap with a metal Jumpman and a perforated heel. A textured leather mudguard and sculpted midsole enhance durability. The lightweight, flexible rubber outsole works a geometric pod pattern.

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Retro Low 'Pure Platinum'
results.story: Originally released in 2015, Jordan Brand brought back the Air Jordan 1 Low ‘Pure Platinum’ in December 2018. Also known as ‘Triple White,’ the monochromatic colorway sees the shoe’s smooth and tumbled leather construction dressed entirely in white with the exception of Jumpman tongue branding and Wings logo at the heel in Pure Platinum.

results.name: Jordan Jumpman Team 2 GS 'Black Pink Foam'
results.story: This version of the Jordan Jumpman Team 2 is a kids' shoe presented in Anthracite, black, Pink Foam and white. Inspired by the Air Jordan 13, the sneaker released in December 2018 with a leather and textile upper, prominent Jordan branding and a heel pull tab for simplified on and off. 'Team Jordan' is displayed vertically on the heel, a forefoot Air-Sole unit promotes responsive cushioning and a paw-like rubber outsole helps with traction on and off the court.

results.name: Jordan Courtside 23 'Concord'
results.story: The Jordan Courtside 23 'Concord' released in December 2018 with design elements inspired by the iconic Air Jordan 3. The sneaker possesses a supportive leather and synthetic upper in white with Jumpman branding in Dark Concord on the tongue and near the ankle. Black covers the shoe's lining, ankle collar, top eyelets and around the toe box, while a visible Air-Sole unit resides within the white midsole. Rounding out the style is an icy blue outsole.

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG 'Origin Story' Special Box
results.story: Released in celebration of Marvel’s Spider-Man: Into the Spider-Verse released in 2018, the Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG 'Origin Story' Special Box features a design that mirrors the pair worn by character Miles Morales, updating the classic Chicago colorway with an icy translucent rubber outsole and a subtle pattern of reflective dots across the shoe’s red leather overlays. The sneaker also comes in a special Marvel-branded box dressed up with various Spider-Man graphics.

results.name: Supreme x Air Jordan 5 Retro 'White' Sample
Air Jordan 1 Retro High 'Noise Cancelling' iD
results.story: Released in 2018, the ‘Noise Cancelling’ pack consists of five iconic Nike silhouettes designed to celebrate New York sports moments so amazing, they silenced the usually bustling city. Shoes from this pack were created to be customization-ready with a removable Swoosh. The Air Jordan 1 Retro High 'Noise Cancelling' pays homage to BMX athlete Nigel Sylvester, who took a leap over the 145th Street Subway station in 2013. The iD (aka 'Nike By You') iterations have been customized to pay homage to an individual who brought silence to the city through their feats of athleticism.

results.name: Air Jordan 33 PF 'Blackout'
results.story: Debuting in 2018, the Air Jordan 33 was the first Jordan without laces, relying instead on a pull system called Fast Fit, as well as a new iteration of FlightSpeed technology. The Air Jordan 33 ‘Blackout’ sneaker adds a black colorway and utility style to the mix, in a futuristic upper that features clear plastic, suede, and mesh overlays. Details include a cheeky “Eject” cord in yellow and a hit of elephant print on the heel, tying this modern look to Air Jordans of the past

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Mid PS 'Dark Concord'
results.story: Made for a big look on little feet, the Nike Air Jordan 1 Mid PS 'Dark Concord' has a tumbled leather upper in an eye-catching purple, with black nubuck suede overlays on the heel and toe cap. The Jordan Wings logo is stamped near the ankle on the heel counter, and the wide polyester textile tongue features a Jumpman logo. Both the midsole and outsole come in rubber for durability and a classic look.

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Mid PS 'Bad Santa'
results.story: The Nike Air Jordan 1 Mid PS 'Bad Santa' sneaker reimagines the 1985 classic with holiday-inspired style. First seen on Michael Jordan during his rookie year with the Chicago Bulls, the AJ1 silhouette became an instant classic, cementing its legacy in sneaker history. The focal point of the synthetic and leather upper is its plaid paneling on the collar, heel and Swoosh areas. Air-Sole cushioning sits atop a rubber outsole for a responsive feel.

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Mid TD 'Dark Concord'
results.story: The Air Jordan 1 Mid TD ‘Dark Concord’ sneaker lends the classic Jordan colorway to smaller sizes in this kids’ iteration. Featuring Dark Concord tumbled leather overlays and Swoosh logo and luxe black nubuck accents, the shoe incorporates the iconic Air Jordan ‘Wings’ logo—as first seen on the OG Air Jordan 1 in 1985—in a barely-there debossed black detail on the ankle, finished with the signature encapsulated Air-Sole unit in the heel.

results.name: Union LA x Air Jordan 1 Retro High NRG 'Storm Blue' Sample
results.story: Unveiled in November 2018, the Jordan Brand and LA-based shop, Union, created a capsule collection inspired by the late 80s and early 90s. The vibe of the collection is influenced by the vintage gear that Union owner Chris Gibbs finds around the Rose Bowl Flea Market and vintage stores. The Union LA x Air Jordan 1 Retro High NRG 'Storm Blue' Sample features a distressed leather upper with exposed stitch detailing and suede on the collar. Below, an Off-White midsole purposely simulates age for a worn in look and feel.

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG 'Rookie of the Year' Sample
Air Jordan 33 GS 'Tech Pack'
results.story: The Air Jordan 33 GS 'Tech Pack' sneaker was released in November 2018, closely following the initial release of the first AJ33 in September of the same year. This 'Tech Pack' edition builds off of a Black synthetic mesh construction, with reinforcing panels at the sides and a FastFit system that replaces the standard laces. The shoe's cushioning incorporates both FlightSpeed and Zoom Air technology for a responsive feel underfoot.

results.name: Jordan Lift Off 'Laser Orange'
results.story: Stylish and sporty, the Air Jordan Lift Off sneaker takes inspiration from the Tinker Hatfield-designed AJ6, a legendary performance basketball sneaker worn by MJ at the 1991 NBA Finals. This ‘Laser Orange’ rendition modernizes the silhouette with street-ready style, dressing its ballistic nylon mesh and suede upper in predominantly Blackened Blue with hits of Laser Orange and fuchsia throughout. A two-tone, sculpted midsole equipped with foam cushioning and a visible Air-Sole unit reinforce the design.

results.name: Jordan Super.Fly MVP PF 'Dark Concord'
results.story: The Jordan Super.Fly debuted in 2012 with a lightweight upper, uniquely ridged midsole, and vents on the upper for breathability. Since then, it’s gone through many iterations, and the Jordan Super.Fly MVP PF 'Dark Concord' represents its evolution. The upper has a mesh base wrapped by a large overlay—minus the vents—made of synthetic material atop a dual-tone React midsole.

Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG NRG 'Not For Resale' Sample
Air Jordan 33 'Guo Ailun' PE
results.story: In May 2017, Guo Ailun signed a deal with the Jordan Brand, effectively becoming the first Chinese player to join the fold. The Air Jordan 33 'Guo Ailun' PE is a kids'-sized takedown of the adult shoe that was released in April 2019. To honor Ailun, this rendition includes a white, quilted panel at the tongue and black Chinese characters on the pull tab. This version retains the modern FastFit entry and knit upper of the original AJ33, first seen in 2018.

Air Jordan 33 'Future of Flight'
results.story: Jordan Brand brings new technology to the table with the latest signature Air Jordan release. The Air Jordan 33 'Future of Flight' features cutting-edge FastFit technology for a lockdown fit and wide range of motion. Dressed in white, the sneaker also sports a mesh upper with black accents on the forefoot side, oversized tongue and heel, and on the collar lining. For a pop of color, the sneaker showcases red details on the elastic eyelets and a translucent outsole.

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Retro Mid GS 'Pure Platinum'
Air Jordan 7 Retro Low NRG 'Bordeaux'
results.story: Paying tribute to the original colorway of the Bordeaux Air Jordan 7s, Nike released a low-top version in this fall 2018 update. The Air Jordan 7 Retro Low NRG 'Bordeaux' features a Light Graphite nubuck upper with black nubuck overlays and perforations along the midfoot for breathability. Design touches include the multicolor geometric patterns on the inner neoprene bootie and outsole, the ‘23’ shield logo at the heel, Bordeaux accents on the throat and jeweled black accents on the midsole.

results.name: Air Jordan 7 Retro Low NRG 'Taxi'
results.story: September 2018 saw Jordan Brand drop three colorways of the Air Jordan 7 Retro Low: one in Concord, another in Bordeaux and, in the case of this yellow model, the third in Taxi. Unlike previous iterations of the AJ7, which favored colorful geometric patterns, this design delivers a clean Taxi yellow across the leather upper and neoprene inner sleeve. Contrast can be found on the sole, where bright shapes share space with a green Jumpman logo.

Air Jordan 1 Mid PS 'Black Cone'
results.story: Drawing inspiration from the original, the Air Jordan 1 Mid PS sneaker puts a modern spin on the sneaker that started an on-court sensation back in 1985. This 'Black Cone' kids' iteration—debuted in September 2018—continues the legacy in a color block leather upper with a nylon tongue, a heel tab and lace closure. A debossed Wings logo and Swooshes add a time-honored element. The two-tone Air-Sole mimics the adult platform.

results.story: The Air Jordan 1 Retro Mid GS 'Bordeaux' dresses an updated version of Michael Jordan's iconic first signature sneaker with a two-tone colorway. Bordeaux covers its premium upper, which stays true to the 1985 OG. Released in August 2018, the kids' shoe displays the Jumpman logo on the tongue and heel, the Wings logo near the ankle and the Nike Swoosh on the quarter panel. Sail coats the midsole and outsole, the latter which possesses a pivot point tread pattern to help with traction.

Jordan CP3.XI 'Dallas Cowboys'
results.story: Released in August 2018, in the lead-up to football season, the Jordan CP3.XI ‘Dallas Cowboys’ celebrates Chris Paul’s favorite NFL team. The performance basketball shoe is dressed in the official colors of the NFL franchise also known as ‘America’s Team.’ A sculpted grey suede upper is accented with an adjustable midfoot strap finished in navy blue and white stripes, along with a small silver Jumpman.

results.name: Jordan Why Not Zer0.1 Low PF 'Cement'
results.story: Russell Westbrook’s signature Jordan Why Not Zer0.1 PF reworks Nike’s iconic Cement color palette, which appears on the upper as well as the midsole. The greyscale design forgoes the usual forefoot strap, while the aesthetic itself features a lower cut than the original. The shoe also sports a toggle lacing system and an inner bootie design.

results.name: Air Jordan 4 'Florida Gators' PE
results.story: The Air Jordan 4 'Florida Gators' PE is a rare, player exclusive edition provided to the University of Florida's football team in 2018 as it prepared to face the Michigan Wolverines in the Peach Bowl. It presents the iconic AJ4—first seen in 1989 and designed by Tinker Hatfield—with a blue suede upper and the Gators logo on the tongue. The sneaker features the Jumpman in orange on the heel, clear wings with a paint splatter design and an icy blue outsole.

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Retro High BG 'Red Black'
results.story: The Air Jordan 1 Retro High BG 'Red Black' reintroduces an iconic silhouette with colors that are familiar to the sneaker. Released in 2016, this shoe's colorway of Gym Red, black and white are similar to the Chicago Bulls' colors that inspired the first AJ1 that debuted in 1985. Like the OG, this shoe comes with Jordan branding, a leather upper that promotes comfort, and cushioning to help maintain support on and off the court.
