Jordan Formula 23 Toggle 'Dark Stucco'
results.story: The Jordan Formula 23 Toggle 'Dark Stucco' features a Dark Stucco neoprene upper with matching leather details on the heel for structure. The low top also sports black accents on the padded neoprene collar with visible stitching, a toggle lacing system that wraps around the heel, black Flywire technology for structure, and a chunky textured midsole.

results.name: Jordan Westbrook 0 'Holiday'
results.story: The Jordan Westbrook 0 'Holiday' is an updated take on Jordan Brand's first lifestyle signature sneaker for 2017 NBA MVP Russell Westbrook. Released in June 2017, the shoe comes with a leather and synthetic upper, Jumpman branding on its padded tongue and a colorway of black, Infrared 23 and Light Bone. The inner tongue displays Westbrook's signature, a crest print resides on the insole and lace jewels of 'WHY' and 'NOT?' share the point guard's mantra.

results.name: Jordan Flight Club 91 'Dandelion'
results.story: Michael Jordan conquered his first NBA championship title in 1991 while boasting his signature Nike Air Jordan 6 silhouette, pushing the sneaker into superstar status. Fast forwarding to February 2013, the classic is back with the Jordan Flight Club 91 sneaker. Sporting a layered leather and suede upper with visible air, this version features a black and red exterior with a pop of Dandelion on its insoles.

results.name: Jordan Trainer 2 Flyknit 'Hyper Jade'
results.story: The Jordan Trainer 2 Flyknit ‘Hyper Jade’ is one of the silhouette’s original colorways released in 2017. The design’s Flyknit upper is dipped in black with Hyper Jade accenting the Flywire, mini Jumpman branding, and translucent outsole. The shoe’s standout feature; however, is a monocoque midfoot strap/midsole combination that stands out in Cool Grey.

results.name: PSNY x Air Jordan 12 Retro 'Paris'
results.story: Fashion label PSNY teamed up on another special rendition with Jordan Brand, this time utilizing the Jordan 12 as their creative canvas. Part of a city capsule that also paid homage to New York and Milan, the Paris offering is decked out in a tonal burgundy hue that covers the entire makeup. Public School branding emerges on the insole and heel.

results.name: PSNY x Air Jordan 12 Retro GS 'NYC' Sample
results.story: Thanks to a number of collaborations between Public School NY and Jordan Brand, the New York-based fashion label has developed a reputation for creating premium interpretations of Air Jordan sneakers. This grade school version of PSNY’s take on the Air Jordan 12 features leather and suede construction, metallic lace eyelets and embossed Jumpman and PSNY co-branding on the tongue. The shoe comes with suede Public School tags, while the laces are fitted with PSNY-branded metal caps. ‘Jumpman’ lettering, embossed on a midfoot panel, is a reminder of the upscale design’s basketball heritage.

results.name: Converse x Air Jordan 2 Retro 'Alumni'
results.story: Converse and Jordan Brand collaborated on a two-pair collection that combines the classic Air Jordan 2 with the Converse Fastbreak. The Air Jordan 2 Retro 'Alumni' draws inspiration from the pair of shoes he wore during a 1986 Carolina Pro Alumni Game. The sneaker boasts a white leather upper with perforations along the midfoot and a snakeskin-like texture on the ankle. The mid-top also sports Carolina Blue accents on the heel and red accents on the outsole.

results.name: PSNY x Air Jordan 12 Retro 'NYC'
results.story: Part of the ‘City Pack’ from Jordan Brand and Public School, this New York edition of the Air Jordan 12 Retro launched as a regional exclusive in June 2017, dropping alongside accompanying Paris and Milan colorways. The monochromatic design features a premium nubuck upper in Wheat, coupled with a gum rubber outsole to resemble a traditional work boot. Public School branding appears on the aglets and custom sock liners, as well as the embossed ‘PSNY’ that runs down the tongue.

results.name: Jordan Trainer 2 Flyknit 'Chicago Bulls'
results.story: Drawing influence from Jordan Brand’s basketball heritage, the Trainer 2 Flyknit is prepared with a ‘Bred’ color scheme that features Gym Red and black tones on the upper’s Flyknit formation. The knit design helps promote forefoot flexibility with its sock-like fit, while the Flywire cables and midfoot strap increase support. The shoe is injected with Zoom Air technology underfoot.

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG 'Legends of the Summer - Red Sparkle'
Air Jordan 13 Retro 'Defining Moments'
results.story: Celebrating the 20th anniversary of Michael Jordan’s final championship season with the Chicago Bulls, this colorway was released as part of the Defining Moments two-pack. The white leather upper is highlighted by metallic gold on the mudguard, heel and midsole. The hologram on the ankle sports the number ’98’—the year of Jordan’s last finals—while the words ‘THEY CAN’T WIN’ and ‘UNTIL WE QUIT’ appear on inside of the left and right tongues. A black and gold colorway makes up the other half of the collection.

results.name: Air Jordan 14 Retro 'Defining Moments'
results.story: One half of the Defining Moments pack that celebrated the 20th anniversary of Michael Jordan’s last season in Chicago, this Air Jordan 14 retro sports a black leather upper accented by a metallic gold midfoot plate. The color also appears on the Jumpman on the ankle, while red accents appear at the heel. The ‘23’ that traditionally appears on the heel is replaced by ’98,’ the year of Jordan’s final title. 'THEY CAN’T WIN’ and ‘UNTIL WE QUIT’ are printed in Varsity Red on the left and right inner tongues. The shoe released alongside a white Air Jordan 13.

results.name: Air Jordan 14 Retro BG 'Defining Moments'
results.story: The Air Jordan 14 Retro BG 'Defining Moments' is one of a two-sneaker pack that commemorates Michael Jordan's sixth (and last) championship with the Chicago Bulls, during which he wore both AJ13s and AJ14s. This shoe comes in a black, premium leather upper with a perforated vamp, toe and midpanel overlays and gold accents. The phrases 'they can't win' and 'until we win' are found on the inside of the tongue.

results.name: Air Jordan 4 Retro GT 'Linen'
results.story: In 2017, Nike released an updated colorway of the iconic 2006 Linen Air Jordan 4. This time, however, the sneaker is primarily dedicated to grade school sizes. The Air Jordan 4 Retro GT 'Linen’ features a white leather upper with mesh window panels on the side and forefoot for breathability. The sneaker also sports Linen leather details on the side, heel, collar and tongue lining, and well as on the cushioning midsole.

results.name: Air Jordan 7 Retro TD 'Pure Money'
results.story: Drawing inspiration from Michael Jordan’s trove of color schemes, Jordan Brand decided to bring back a fan-favorite palette with the Air Jordan 7 Retro TD 'Pure Money.' The sneaker features a white-based leather upper, metallic silver leather overlays, and perforations on the sidewall for breathability. The sneaker also sports a Pure Platinum toe cap, a traditional lacing system for a lockdown fit, and a perforated midsole.

results.name: Air Jordan 11 Retro Low TD 'Barons'
results.story: In 2017, Jordan Brand released this clean black and white ‘Barons’ colorway of the Air Jordan 11 Low in sizes for the whole family. Designed to pay tribute to Michael’s baseball career, the TD version is clad entirely in black nubuck, while its larger counterparts feature a patent leather mudguard wrap. Like the others in the lineup, it features metallic silver embroidered branding over a crisp white midsole and translucent outsole.

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Retro High BP 'Gym Red'
Air Jordan 12 Retro PS 'Black Deadly Pink'
Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG 'Wings' Sample
Air Jordan 1 Retro High 'Thank You NYC'
results.story: Part of Jordan Brand’s RE2PECT collection celebrating Derek Jeter, the Air Jordan 1 Retro High ‘Thank You NYC’ was featured at a pop-up shop in New York City in 2017. Appearing in a New York Yankees-inspired color palette, the all-white leather construction is complemented by navy laces and grey on the outsole and sockliner. A laser-etched ‘Thank You NYC’ stands out on the heel, with the ‘Wings’ logo emerging on the ankle in a similar fashion.

results.name: Air Jordan 4 Retro TD 'Pure Money'
results.story: Released in toddler sizing, the 2017 Air Jordan 4 Retro TD 'Pure Money' hit the shelves just in time for the summer months. The sneaker features a premium white leather upper with matching mesh window panels along the sides and forefoot for breathability. The sneaker also sports “Pure$” lettering under the back tabs, metallic accents on the upper eyelets, and a polyurethane foam midsole for lightweight and long-lasting cushioning.

results.name: Air Jordan 5 Retro 'Fab Five' PE
results.story: This Air Jordan 5 Retro PE was designed by Tinker Hatfield and Dan Sunwoo to pay tribute to the Michigan Wolverines’ unforgettable ‘Fab Five’ team of the ‘90s which included Chris Webber, Jalen Rose, Juwan Howard, Jimmy King, and Ray Jackson. This sought-after Players Edition features signature Michigan team colors throughout in addition to signature elements including “Hail To” and “The Victors” stitched on the right and left tongue labels as well as a Fab Five hand gesture graphic logo on the heels.

results.name: Air Jordan 7 Retro PS 'Hyper Pink'
results.story: This polarizing Air Jordan 7 Retro PS was released exclusively to the kid’s lineup as part of a ‘Hyper Pink’ Pack that included matching versions of the Air Jordan 6 and Air Jordan 13 in 2017. With its premium leather upper dipped entirely in black, Hyper Pink accents are left to take over branding elements at the tongue, ankle, heel, and jagged midsole.

results.name: Air Jordan 7 Retro TD 'Pantone'
results.story: Drawing inspiration from Michael Jordan’s University of North Carolina alma mater, the Air Jordan 7 Retro TD ‘Pantone’ appears with a University Blue rendering on the upper’s nubuck construction. White accents emerge on the midsole and Jumpman branding to provide a good color contrast.

results.name: Air Jordan 7 Retro TD 'Hyper Pink'
results.story: Jordan Brand readies Michael Jordan’s seventh silhouette in a toddler-specific offering that’s prepared with a black tumbled leather application. Accented by Hyper Pink on the midsole and Jumpman branding, Air is encapsulated in the midsole. Jordan himself wore the 7 during the 1992 season, when he led the Bulls to another championship as well as the US to a gold medal at the Barcelona Games.

results.name: Air Jordan 7 Retro PS 'Pantone'
results.story: The Air Jordan 7 Retro PS ‘Pantone’ celebrates Michael Jordan’s playing days with the University of North Carolina Tar Heels, featuring a University Blue rendering on the upper’s leather construction. Contrasting white accents appear on the Jumpman logos and midsole, while the Air cushioning is hidden inside the angular midsole design.

results.name: Jordan Trainer Prime 'Pure Platinum'
results.story: Appearing in this ‘Pure Platinum’ color scheme, the Jordan Trainer Prime is designed with a sleek mesh upper construction that’s meant to increase ventilation. The sockliner features a Dynamic Fit neoprene application, while the Cushlon midsole gives way to triangular flex grooves on the outsole.

results.name: Jordan 6 Rings GS 'Pink Flash'
results.story: Released exclusively in girls grade school sizing, the Jordan 6 gets an eccentric colorway with retro qualities. The Jordan 6 Rings GS 'Pink Flash' features a smooth white leather upper with Pure Platinum overlays on the lace system and Pink Flash accents on the heel and tongue branding. The sneaker also boasts an ankle strap linked to the lace cage for a locked down fit.

results.name: Jordan Express
results.story: The Jordan Express is a lifestyle offering that borrows subtle design details from the Jordan 4, including the lines of the midsole and the grid-like caging system that helps wrap the foot. Equipped with a white and Ice Blue color scheme that gives the nod to Michael Jordan’s University of North Carolina alma mater, the shoe also implements a sleek mesh upper supported by an asymmetrical lacing system.

results.name: Jordan Express 'Gym Red'
results.story: Introduced in 2017, the Jordan Express combines minimalistic styling with ergonomic innovation. Seen here in a classic red, white, and black combination, the lifestyle silhouette features a one-piece mesh upper with slip-on functionality and a synthetic heel wrap for added security. Underfoot, Phylon foam offers a lightweight, cushioned ride atop strategically placed rubber outsole pods for grip.

results.name: Jordan Express
results.story: The Jordan Express borrows familiar designs details from some of the most iconic Jordans ever seen on the court. Featuring a Triple White color scheme, the shoe incorporates the multi-eyelet wing-flap that’s similar to the Jordan 4, while the asymmetrical lacing system resembles the Jordan 10. The shoe is also constructed with a sock-like design that wraps the midfoot, with mesh paneling to promote breathability.

results.name: Jordan Express 'Triple Black'
results.story: Borrowing inspiration from the Jordan 4, the Jordan Express is rendered in a Triple Black color scheme with a customizable eyelet flange that mirrors the makeup of the classic basketball shoe. The rest of the upper is formed with a sock-like design and sleek mesh paneling, and the midsole incorporates a similar look as the 4. The lacing system implements an asymmetrical design.

results.name: Jordan Express
results.story: Taking key design details from the Jordan 4, the Jordan Express features a black mesh upper with a sock-like construction and a white lacing cage that allows for a more customized fit. The midsole also mimics the Jordan 4’s iconic shape, while the familiar Jumpman logo is stamped on the heel.

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Retro High GG 'Blue Moon'
results.story: Making its way to the girls’ grade school lineup in 2017, this Air Jordan 1 Retro High GG is distinguished by a unique color blocking technique at the heel. Released alongside a complementary hot pink variation, the Blue Moon and Pure Platinum high-top sports a material mixture of canvas and suede across the upper. A white midsole offers contrast against the color-blocked section in aqua while a matching Blue Moon outsole finishes off the look underneath.

results.name: Jordan Super.Fly 5 PO
results.story: Emerging with a Chicago Bulls colorway, the Jordan Super.Fly 5 PO used Blake Griffin’s explosiveness on the court as their inspiration for the design. The black mesh upper is constructed with a light and flexible formation, while the white and red midfoot strap promotes stability and matches the appearance of the mudguard. The midsole sports Zoom Air cushioning in the forefoot, with foam pods in the inner sleeve.

results.name: CP3.X AE 'Playoffs'
results.story: Designed for the postseason in 2017, Chris Paul’s signature CP3.X AE was first unveiled in this ‘Playoffs’ colorway. A neutral base, gold accents, and gum outsole give it a casual look, but the court shoe sports performance features like a lightweight seamless woven upper, Flywire cables for support, and a structured midsole/outsole for responsiveness and quick cuts.

results.name: Air Jordan 4 Retro TD 'Motorsports'
results.story: Re-emerging in March 2017, the Air Jordan 4 Retro TD 'Motorsports' sneaker was originally released as a Friends and Family edition to Michael Jordan’s fledgling racing team in celebration of its four-year anniversary. This kids' edition sees the full-grain leather upper decorated with the usual combination of Game Royal eyestays and a quarter cage. Jumpman icons are mirrored on the tongue and heel. The signature midsole and rubber outsole repeat the palette.

results.name: Jordan Melo M13 Energy 'Sunset Glow'
results.story: Designed to honor Carmelo Anthony’s career, the Jordan Melo M13 Energy 'Sunset Glow' features a dynamic Sunset Glow upper with a traditional lace-up closure. The sneaker also sports a padded mesh inner sleeve for a breathable and lightweight feel, brown accents on the Jumpman branding, FlightSpeed technology for added comfort, and Zoom Air in the midsole for responsive cushioning and impact protection.

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Retro High BG 'Soar'
results.story: Over 30 years since the silhouette hit shelves in 1985, this 2017 iteration of the Air Jordan 1 showcases one of the early samples come to life. The Air Jordan 1 Retro High BG features a Soar leather upper with black accents on the perforated toe box, tongue, liner, and Swoosh branding. The basketball sneaker also boasts white side panels, an encapsulated Air-Sole unit in the heel for lightweight cushioning. The Jordan Wings logo that has graced the AJ1 for years is replaced with “Air Jordan” lettering on the collar, a nod to an early sample or prototype that Jordan had for an early photo shoot in his rookie season.

results.name: Air Jordan 13 Retro CB 'Hyper Pink' Gift Pack
results.story: This Air Jordan 13 Retro is a kids' shoe released as part of a 'Crib Gift Pack' that also included a knit cap with the iconic Jumpman logo. While the AJ 13 debuted in 1997, this 2016 version stays true to OG design, which was inspired by Michael Jordan's 'Black Cat' nickname. Black and Anthracite coat the majority of this shoe, which comes with a leather and synthetic upper, the model's holographic eye, Hyper Pink accents and an outsole resembling a panther paw.

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Retro High GT 'Mint Foam'
Remade x 400ml x Air Jordan 4 Retro 'Chinese New Year'
results.story: Requiring approximately 20 hours to assemble, the Remade x 400ml x Air Jordan 4 Retro ‘Chinese New Year’ is a custom creation celebrating the lunar calendar holiday. Clad in premium red leather, the mid-top features a number of special details, including fish-scale detailing, ‘Happy New Year’ in Chinese on the tongue and a heel emblem that showcases a gold-plated Chinese character for ‘wealth.’

results.name: Jordan Son Of Mars Low 'Black'
results.story: The Air Jordan Son Of Mars Low sneaker is an Air Jordan Spizike-inspired silhouette that blends popular 90s Air Jordan models together. This 'Black' version sports an all-black combination leather and synthetic upper with perforated side panels. An AJ3-inspired elephant print adorns the heel tab and midsole, while a two-tone outsole with two Air-Sole units at the heel deliver cushioned comfort underfoot.

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Retro High GG 'Mulberry'
results.story: The Air Jordan 1 Retro High GG 'Mulberry' was created exclusively in grade school sizes and released in 2015. Mulberry covers most of the premium upper, while Blue Lagoon is found on the tongue's Jumpman logo and laces. Dark grey and black round out the colorway of this shoe, which prominently displays the Wings logo and Nike Swoosh. A white midsole provides contrast with black returning on the outsole, complete with the standard AJ1 pivot point tread pattern.

results.name: Jordan Trainer 1
results.story: Inspired by the original makeup of the Jordan 1, the Jordan Trainer 1 is a mid-top design that sports a neoprene bootie system around the heel collar. The rest of the upper displays a black mesh construction that’s accented with a tonal elephant print, while the Flywire cables promote a locked-down fit. Contrasted with Infrared tones on the Jordan branding and midsole, the outsole implements a low-profile design that utilizes a strategic siping pattern to increase traction.

results.name: Jordan Jasmine Premium HC GG 'Pearl Heiress'
Jordan Eclipse 'Cool Grey'
results.story: Released in December 2016, this iteration of the Jordan Eclipse is presented in Cool Grey with a low-top cut and a deconstructed textile upper. The lightweight sneaker is equipped with a neoprene tongue, encapsulated Zoom Air in the heel and a low-profile injected midsole that also serves as the outsole. A small Jumpman logo appears on the tongue pull tab, while a larger version is displayed on the heel. The outsole's herringbone pattern helps with traction on multiple surfaces.

results.name: Jordan Trainer 1 Low 'Triple White'
results.story: This edition of the Jordan Trainer 1 Low is presented with a lightweight mesh upper and a color scheme of white and Pure Platinum. Released in December 2016, the 'Triple White' sneaker comes with a stretch-fit collar, heel pull tab, Flywire cables, Jumpman branding and subtle elephant print. A Zoom Air unit in the heel helps with responsive cushioning, while an icy blue outsole offers a traction pattern created for a variety of workouts.

results.name: Jordan Melo M13 'Varsity Red'
results.story: Carmelo Anthony received his 13th signature shoe from Jordan Brand, the Jordan Melo M13. Featuring a mesh-based Varsity Red upper with an engineered mesh overlay, rubberized synthetic details are interspersed in a pattern on the upper. The sneaker also sports a padded tongue for comfort, an elasticated lacing system for a personalized fit, and a Zoom Air cushioning unit in the midsole for comfort and support.

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Retro Hi TD 'Deep Royal Blue'
Jordan Eclipse Chukka 'Black'
results.story: Building off of Nike Roshe, the Jordan Eclipse Chukka draws from a series of sources, including the classic Chukka boot that dates back to the traditional footwear of the British army. The Jordan Eclipse Chukka features a black woven textile upper with a braided pattern and a neoprene throat for an adaptive fit. The sneaker also sports Air technology in the midsole for lightweight cushioning and a branded heel with the Jumpman logo in Dark Grey.

results.name: Jordan True Flight GP
results.story: Mirroring the design of the Jordan 7, the Jordan True Flight appears as a kids’ lifestyle offering with heritage basketball elements incorporated into the design. Featuring a premium nubuck construction that’s comprised of black and Rio Teal tones, the sneaker is accented with gold Jumpman branding throughout. A mesh tongue is included for breathability.

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Retro High NYC '23NY' Sample
Jordan Flight Origin 3 'Black'
results.story: Boasting various modified Air Jordan design details, the Jordan Flight Origin blends old school style with contemporary construction. Nike’s Jordan Flight Origin 3 'Black' sneaker expands upon the franchise featuring an allover tonal colorway, accented with printed laces and contrast Jumpman logos on the tongue and heel. Underfoot, the shoe is supported with lightweight cushioning and a durable treaded outsole.

results.name: CP3.X 'Space Jam'
results.story: This CP3.X 'Space Jam' draws inspiration from the original release of the Air Jordan 11 Space Jam. The sneaker features a black Flywire upper accented with Concord hits and white speckling. The low-top also sports a full-length Air unit, a TPU cage on the side panels and a solid rubber outsole. The celestial design on the side panels serves as a nod to the zodiac signs of Paul’s family.

results.name: Jordan True Flight 'Black'
results.story: The Air Jordan True Flight offers a new spin on the Air Jordan 7, featuring a lighter composition and a full-length Air unit. The retro-inspired design also includes a herringbone outsole and a neoprene Dynamic Fit sleeve. This simple black and white colorway sports a metallic gold Jumpman at the ankle.

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Retro Mid 'Ice Blue'
results.story: Released during the 2017 NCAA Tournament, the ‘Ice Blue’ edition of the Air Jordan 1 Retro Mid gives off University of North Carolina vibes. The Varsity Royal upper combines with Ice Blue on the toe box, heel and Swoosh to complete a colorway similar to Michael Jordan’s college alma mater. Varsity Royal also appears on the ‘Wings’ logo, Jumpman on the heel and outsole, while a white midsole provides a crisp contrast.

results.name: Air Jordan 6 'First Championship'
results.story: This Air Jordan 6 is inspired by goalkeeper Tim Howard and celebrates the US Men’s National Soccer team. The shoe features a white leather base that is covered in 3M reflective material, complemented with speckled navy midsole accents and translucent touches on the tongue, heel, and outsole. The shoe itself never officially hit the market and there is expected to only be around 30 pairs floating around amongst the general public.

results.name: Jordan True Flight
results.story: Cool Grey, a popular color on heritage Jordan offerings, makes its way onto the Jordan True Flight. Constructed with nubuck paneling on the majority of the upper, the shoe is equipped with a mesh tongue for enhanced breathability, while the design itself borrows inspiration from the Jordan 7’s aesthetic. The white outsole contrasts the look.

results.name: Jordan Eclipse 'Cool Grey'
results.story: Made for off-court wear, the Jordan Eclipse features a minimalist soft knit upper in heathered grey. Embellishments are limited to an extended fabric tongue loop and Jumpman branding on the heel panel. The lightweight build up top is mounted on a contrasting white cupsole, equipped with an Air Sole unit at the heel and a herringbone traction outsole pattern for multidirectional traction.

results.name: Jordan True Flight 'Black'
results.story: Taking inspiration from the iconic design of the Air Jordan 7, the Jordan True Flight updates the heritage basketball sneaker with a lifestyle appeal, featuring a Triple Black color scheme and nubuck paneling throughout the upper construction. Resting on an Air Sole unit for cushioning, the shoe also utilizes a herringbone pattern on the outsole for traction.

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Retro High BG 'Deep Royal Blue'
Air Jordan 1 Retro High GG 'Fierce Purple'
results.story: Originally released in 1985, Jordan Brand gave the Air Jordan 1 High a vibrant facelift in 2016 with the release of this ‘Fierce Purple’ colorway. The high-top stands out with a jacquard textile base with purple leather overlays and red Jumpman and Swoosh branding. The revamped upper rides atop a full-length white midsole and matching purple rubber outsole.

results.name: Jordan Trainer 1 GS 'Banned'
results.story: The Jordan Trainer 1 GS 'Banned' features a black-based mesh upper with Gym Red embroidery dressed in a cheetah-like print. The low top also sports Flywire cables integrated with the laces, black leather accents on the eyestay, an injected Phylon midsole with a Zoom Air unit, and a neoprene inner sleeve for an adaptive fit.

results.name: Air Jordan 7 Retro BT 'Tinker Alternate'
results.colorway: White/Deep Royal Blue-Fiery Red-Metallic Gold Coin

results.name: Jordan Dub Zero GS 'Black Wolf Grey'
results.story: Sharing the anatomy of two iconic brand styles, the Air Jordan Dub Zero GS finds a voice of its own through fresh graphics and a distinct textile mix. This 'Oreo' kids' edition is taken over by a leather upper with a laser-etched lateral panel, a textured tongue and nubuck heel. A synthetic heel pull—extracted from the Air Jordan 6—aids entry. An Air-encapsulating midsole and rubber outsole carry an Air Jordan 3-inspired vibe.

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Mid Premium GS 'Black Dark Grey'
Laika x Air Jordan 15 Retro 'Kubo and the Two Strings'
Air Jordan 1 Retro High BP 'Gold Medal'
Air Jordan 1 Retro High TD 'Gold Medal'
results.story: This toddler edition of the Air Jordan 1 Retro High ‘Gold Medal’ released ahead of the 2016 Olympic Games in Rio. Featuring Deep Royal Blue on the overlays, the rest of the upper’s leather construction sports a white base with Metallic Gold Coin accents on the Swoosh and ‘Wings’ branding. The nylon tongue adds a retro appeal, while the heel loop enables easy on and off.

results.name: Jordan Eclipse 'White Infrared'
results.story: A lifestyle silhouette, the Jordan Eclipse takes on a straightforward two-tone colorway on its breathable mesh upper. The shoe’s tongue, vamp and laces are finished in bright Infrared 23, while the overlay that wraps around the quarter panel and heel is rendered in contrasting white. A gold Jumpman adorns the heel, and a speckled midsole packs an encapsulated Air Sole unit for a cushioned ride.

results.name: Jordan Academy 'Infrared'
results.story: The Air Jordan Academy 'Infrared' sneaker adds a futuristic feel to the Jordan Brand lineup. The shoe’s unique, textured upper is constructed from a lightweight textile fabrication, with a supportive ankle strap and convenient stretch-gore laces for easy on-off access. Flexible cushioning is provided through the injected Air-Sole unit, while a non-marking rubber outsole with a strategic pattern underfoot helps with traction.

results.name: Jordan Reveal GS
results.story: Jordan Brand remixes their basketball heritage into a lifestyle sneaker with the Jordan Reveal. Featuring a Triple Black color scheme, the shoe is formed with seamless mesh paneling and a sock-like fit, while rope laces add to the utilitarian look. Tonal Jumpman icons stand out on the tongue and heel, while color arrives via the Infrared 23 insole.

results.name: Jordan Hydro 5 Retro Slide 'White Metallic Gold'
Air Jordan 12 Retro TD 'Hyper Jade'
results.story: The ‘Hyper Jade’ edition of the Air Jordan 12 dropped in sizes for the whole family during July 2016. The design features a black nubuck upper with textured turquoise leather overlays and metallic silver Jumpman branding.

results.name: Jordan Reveal 'Metallic Gold Coin'
results.story: The Jordan Reveal brings minimalist style to an off-court silhouette supported with Nike Air cushioning. The streamlined design is accentuated with a clean white colorway, executed on a breathable mesh upper with a tonal white leather overlay that wraps around the heel. The pristine finish is accented with metallic gold Jumpman logos and matching gold speckling on the midsole.

results.name: Air Jordan 12 Retro PS 'University Blue'
results.story: Released in 2016, the Air Jordan 12 Retro PS 'University Blue' is an updated take on the Michael Jordan signature first seen in 1996. This edition, a durable kids' shoe, presents University Blue on the tongue's Jumpman, Midnight Navy on the lining, and a combination of the two on the heel tag with Jordan branding. Wolf Grey takes over the tongue, laces and premium upper, while white covers the mudguard and most of the midsole and outsole.

results.name: Jordan Trainer ST 'University Blue'
results.story: Jordan expands upon their training-specific footwear offerings with the Trainer ST, which is rendered in a University Blue and Midnight Navy color scheme that’s contrasted with Infrared 23 accents on the Jumpman logo and outsole. The upper is constructed with a breathable mesh knit on the toe and tongue, while the iconic cement print is woven into the design for a heritage look. The midsole features FlightFlex technology.

results.name: Jordan Trainer 1 Low 'Anthracite'
results.story: The Jordan Trainer 1 Low features a black elephant print jacquard pattern with a contrasting silver Jumpman logo on the side wall. The sneaker also boasts a low cut neoprene bootie for wider range of motion and a contrasting white midsole for responsive cushioning.

results.name: Air Jordan 5 Retro TD 'Pre-Grape'
results.story: More commonly known as the ‘Hornets’ edition, the Nike Air Jordan 5 ‘Pre-Grape’ takes inspiration from an unreleased Tinker Hatfield sample from the 1990s. The design sports a navy leather upper with grey and turquoise accents and a 3M reflective tongue. Released in 2015, the sneaker’s trademark shark teeth stand out in turquoise atop an icy translucent outsole.

results.name: Jordan Jumpman Team 2 Premium BP 'Black Electric Green'
Jordan Ultra Fly
results.story: The Jordan Ultra Fly sports an engineered mesh upper with Kurim cage-like overlays across the upper. The low top also sports Hyper Turquoise accents on the 9-chamber Zoom Air unit and inner sleeve. An oversized reflective silver Jumpman logo takes over the medial heel, completing the look.

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Retro Hi Prem BG 'Red Elephant'
results.story: Uniting elements from the Air Jordan 3, this Air Jordan 1 Retro is equipped with a primarily red leather upper with elephant print accents along the toe, eyestay, and heel. The high-top design provides superior ankle support, while the toe is etched with a perforated panel for ventilation.

results.name: Jordan Air Spike Forty 'Dunk From Above'
results.story: Continuing Jordan Brand’s relationship with filmmaker Spike Lee, the Jordan Air Spike Forty ‘Dunk From Above’ released in March 2016. The silhouette takes direct inspiration from the Air Jordan 5, highlighted by a lace toggle, translucent rubber outsole and reflective 3M, applied here on the shoe’s Midnight Navy leather overlays. Additional design details include a Gold Leaf mesh upper and a Phylon midsole packing a Zoom Air unit in the heel.

results.name: Air Jordan 12 Retro TD 'Vivid Pink'
results.story: The Air Jordan 12 Retro TD ‘Vivid Pink’ released in March 2016. Made for the youngest athlete in the family, the mid-top sneaker sports a simple two-tone design, highlighted by a tumbled white leather upper with contrasting pops of Vivid Pink on the lining, pull loop and textured overlays on the sidewalls. An embroidered Jumpman logo on the tongue delivers a final hit of energetic coloring.

results.name: Jordan Horizon 'Gym Red'
results.story: The Air Jordan Horizon ‘Gym Red’ takes evident influence from the design of the Jordan 13, featuring a seamless Gym Red upper formation that’s blanketed with a honeycomb netting to break up the tonal appearance. An asymmetrical lacing system provides added stability, while the midsole and outsole sport contrasting black.

results.name: Jordan Melo M12 'Dungeon'
results.story: Jordan Brand’s signature shoe for player Carmelo Anthony gets its twelfth release with the M12. The basketball sneaker comes with a flexible mesh upper and asymmetrical loop lacing system. The sole incorporates two Zoom Air units for cushioning and FlightSpeed technology for a responsive energy return.

results.name: Air Jordan 10 Retro BT 'Charlotte Hornets'
results.story: MJ’s Carolina roots show true blue in the Air Jordan 10 Retro BT ‘Charlotte Hornets,’ featuring a color combo inspired by the area NBA team he owns. The adult shoe released on June 18th, 2016, part of a city pack including New York, Chicago and Los Angeles. Tinker Hatfield created the AJ 10 when Jordan was away from hoops, with its flexible toe a hallmark of MJ’s favorite styles and a striped sole paying tribute to his remarkable career achievements.

results.name: Jordan True Flight GT
results.story: The Jordan True Flight GT is a kids' shoe featuring a leather and synthetic upper with a color scheme of Cool Grey, Vivid Pink and Wolf Grey. Its mesh tongue features the iconic Jumpman logo, as does the side panel and heel. Released in 2016, the high-top sneaker comes with a heel tab to ease taking off and putting on, while a streamlined midsole promotes cushioning. Finishing the look is a tri-colored outsole with a multidirectional pattern to help with traction.

results.name: CP3.IX 'Hyper Orange'
results.story: Chris Paul’s signature CP3.IX with Jordan Brand gets a radiant rendering that sports Hyper Orange tones throughout the tongue, sockliner and outsole, while contrasting black hues emerge on the heel and mesh underlays. Complete with lateral outriggers and an inner bootie system for increased stability, the shoe also features a Zoom Air cushioning unit.

results.name: Air Jordan 8 Retro PS 'Chrome'
results.story: The ‘Chrome’ colorway of the Air Jordan 8 Retro PS blacks out the design of the retro basketball sneaker, featuring nubuck paneling on the upper construction and a dual-strap closure system that mimics the lockdown system of the Air Raid. Streaks of Light Graphite complement the design, appearing on the midsole shank, ‘23’ branding and chenille Jumpman on the tongue.

results.name: Air Jordan 8 Retro Infant 'Chrome' Gift Pack
Air Jordan 11 Retro Low BP 'Bred'
results.story: Celebrating both the 30th anniversary of the Jordan Brand and the 20th anniversary of the AJ 11, this variation of the Air Jordan 11 was one of the most highly-anticipated releases of 2015 as it brought back the iconic ‘Bred’ colorway and introduced an all-new low-top format. Like the original, the sneaker shares a predominantly black upper in patent leather and mesh atop a white midsole and translucent outsole in True Red.

results.name: Air Jordan 7 Retro PS 'Mulberry'
results.story: The Air Jordan 7 Retro PS ‘Mulberry’ released in December 2015. Limited to kids’ sizing, the two-tone colorway features a Mulberry nubuck base with contrasting black leather overlays. A nubuck black heel panel is accented with additional pops of Mulberry on a 23-branded heel tab and nylon pull loop. The AJ7’s signature midsole detailing is rendered in a blend of white and Fuchsia Glow.

results.name: Air Jordan 7 Retro TD 'Mulberry'
results.story: This toddler-size Air Jordan 7 appears in the ‘Mulberry’ colorway, featuring the berry-inspired tones on the majority of the upper’s nubuck paneling, while black leather accents are applied to the overlays. The shoe also incorporates a snug inner bootie construction for support, while the pull tabs on the heel allow for easy on and off. Hits of Fuchsia Glow add color to the design.

results.name: Jordan Flight Flex TR 2 GS 'Wolf Grey'
Air Jordan 6 Retro OG BG 'Maroon' 2015
results.story: The Air Jordan 6 Retro OG BG sneaker is an iconic symbol of Michael Jordan's first championship victory in 1991. This December 2015 re-release is presented in an Off-White leather upper accented by strategic placements of Maroon Red. The high-top retains all of its essential design elements with Nike branding throughout and ventilated lateral side panels. Modern tooling includes a TPU heel pull and a clear outsole.

results.name: Air Jordan 6 Retro GS 'Maroon' 2016 International Release
results.story: The Air Jordan 6 GS ‘Maroon’ 2016 International Release debuted with a colorway not seen on retail shelves since 1991. The simple two-tone design makes use of an all-leather upper finished in entirely in an understated shade of Off-White, contrasted by pops of New Maroon on the molded tongue, lace toggle and midsole. Tonal Nike Air embroidery on the heel completes the OG design.

results.name: Air Jordan 8 Retro TD 'Crib Booties Pack'
Air Jordan 6 Retro BT 'Maroon'
results.story: The Air Jordan 6 Retro BT takes design cues from Michael Jordan's prized German sports car. Originally seen in 1991, this 'Maroon' kids' sneaker revives the icon's legacy with a leather upper defined by abstract lines, perforated lateral cutouts and a contrast neoprene tongue. A Jumpman logo, striped heel strap and counter embroidery add distinction to the look.

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Retro High Premium GG 'Phantom'
results.story: The Air Jordan 1 Retro High Premium GG ‘Phantom’ released in November 2015 exclusively in girls’ sizing. The high-top’s upper has a monochromatic color scheme in light tan, executed in a blend of smooth and tumbled leather. The heel is adorned with an embroidered Jumpman logo, as is the woven tag stitched atop a textile tongue. It all rests on contrasting solid white tooling.

results.name: Air Jordan 7 Retro BT 'Nothing But Net'
Air Jordan 7 Retro PS 'Nothing But Net'
Jordan Horizon 'Wolf Grey'
results.story: The Air Jordan Horizon strips down the Air Jordan 13 template, retaining its essential elements. This 'Wolf Grey' iteration is outfitted in a one-piece textile upper with premium leather lining the asymmetrical collar, traditional lacing and minimal Jumpman branding on the tongue. The underfoot platform houses dual Zoom Air units, a carbon fiber shank for midfoot integrity and strategically placed rubber outsole pods.

results.name: Jordan DNA LX 'Black'
results.story: The Jordan DNA LX sneaker is a synthesis of heritage-inspired elements that make up the iconic brand. Forming a flexible fit, this version dons a ribbed Flyknit upper with 'Gym Red' ventilation, traditional lacing threaded through TPU eyestays and a synthetic-leather counter. A Jumpman counter logo denotes the signature line's distinguished legacy. Midsole foam and sculpted rubber outsole tread structure the platform.

results.name: Air Jordan CP3.IX 'Yellow Dragon'
results.story: The Air Jordan CP3.IX 'Yellow Dragon' was released in 2015 as the ninth iteration of Chris Paul's signature shoe. The yellow and black colorway is meant to connect CP3's on-court agility with the dragon dance that's used to celebrate Chinese New Year, with black dragon scales and a partially obscured dragon insignia found on the heel. The nine-chamber Air system in the fore foot creates dynamic push-off, and a specially made outrigger system provides extra stability.

results.name: Air Jordan CP3.IX
results.story: Chris Paul’s signature CP3.IX debuted this Clippers-friendly colorway in 2015. Based in vibrant Soar blue, the mid-top’s Flight Web Fit System constructed upper is highlighted by navy and teal. Other signature details include Infrared branding, a teal outsole, and teal speckling throughout.

results.name: Air Jordan CP3.IX
results.story: Designed exclusively to highlight Chris Paul’s agility on the court, the Air Jordan CP3.IX features a composite mesh upper in black and Anthracite. The sneaker also sports foam overlays for support, a webbing lacing system for an adaptive fit, a nine-chamber Zoom unit for responsive cushioning, and a herringbone pattern on the outsole for traction.

results.name: Air Jordan CP3.IX
results.story: Designed to reflect Chris Paul’s agility on the court, the Air Jordan CP3.IX features a composite mesh upper dressed in black with foam overlays to ensure ultimate support. The sneaker also boasts black leather details, a padded blue mesh tongue for breathability, a webbing lace system for a lockdown fit, nine-chamber Zoom unit, and a herringbone pattern on the outsole for superior traction.

results.name: Jordan 4 Retro MCS 'Gym Red'
results.story: Inspired by the 1994 Air Jordan 4, these Air Jordan 4 MCS Cleats feature a Gym Red tumbled leather upper with a black mesh grate at the midfoot. Contrasting white emerges on the eyestay, Jumpman branding and heel patch as well as the midsole. Phylon foam provides cushioning, while a Power Channel plate sports 12 molded TPU cleats designed for both grass and turf.

results.name: Jordan Spizike GS 'Soar'
results.story: The ‘Soar’ color scheme of the Jordan Spiz’ike features Soar on the upper’s leather formation, while contrasting black accents emerge on the elephant print, tongue and sockliner. The hybrid lifestyle offering blends a series of design details from classic Jordan models, like the cement pattern and midsole from the 3, the wing flaps from the 4, the collar from the 5 and the tongue from the 6.

results.name: Air Jordan 7 Retro PS 'Fuchsia Glow'
results.story: This preschool release presents a simple white and black colorway with Fuchsia Glow and Mulberry accents on the laces, outsole and branding. The white leather upper sports perforations on the side walls, while the multicolor sole houses a hidden Air unit. As the first shoe in the Jordan line to exclude Nike branding, it instead sports a Jumpman, ‘23’ and ‘Jordan’ to mark the look.

results.name: Air Jordan 7 Retro TD 'Fuchsia Glow'
results.story: Toddlers can enjoy the cutting-edge designs of the Air Jordan 7 with this exclusive release. The Air Jordan 7 Retro TD 'Fuchsia Glow' features a white leather upper with perforations on the sides for breathability and matching paneling throughout. The sneaker also sports black details on the throat and ankle, Fuchsia Glow accents on the laces and Jumpman logo, and purple features on the heel tab and midsole plugs.

results.name: Jordan Super.Fly 4 'Fengshui'
results.story: The ‘Feng Shui’ edition of the Jordan Super.Fly 4 appears in the Charlotte Hornets’ team colors, featuring a combination of Bright Concord and Blue Lagoon tones throughout the upper’s mesh construction. The sneaker is finished with the Chinese characters for Feng Shui across the insoles, while a white outsole provides a clean finish.

results.name: Jordan Super.Fly 4
results.story: Jordan Brand drops Infrared tones onto the design of the Jordan Super.Fly 4, featuring a mostly Hyperfuse construction on the upper. Leather accents on the tongue and heel add a premium finish to the makeup, while white accents on the Jumpman branding and orange tones on the sockliner provide subtle contrast.

results.name: Air Jordan 14 Retro Low TD 'Laney' 2015
results.story: The Little Air Jordan 14 Low adapts elements of the sports car-inspired adult original for small feet. Issued in October 2015, this 'Laney' version's unofficial namesake is borrowed from Michael Jordan's high school alma mater due to its Varsity Royal nubuck shroud with Jumpman icons and metal eyelets. An elongated tongue and internal lacing give it a distinctive look. The foam midsole and rubber outsole provide cushioning and stability.

results.name: Jordan Westbrook 0
results.story: Unveiled on the feet of Russell Westbrook at New York Fashion Week in July 2015, this Cool Grey version of the Jordan Westbrook 0 is one of a handful of original colorways for the Oklahoma City point guard’s first signature sneaker. The lifestyle design reflects Russell’s appreciation for fashion and features layered premium leather with embossed details, webbed lacing, and a white vulcanized sole.

results.name: Jordan Westbrook 0
results.story: The Jordan Westbrook 0 applies a monochromatic finish to the upper of Russell Westbrook’s lifestyle silhouette. The shoe’s simple color scheme is enhanced with a suede upper and a subtle reptilian texture on the tonal leather mudguard. Metallic gold on the lace jewels—spelling out Russell Westbrook’s ‘Why Not?’ motto—offers contrasting pops of color. It all rests on a clean white rubber midsole.

results.name: Jordan Westbrook 0 'Military Green'
results.story: Russell Westbrook’s 0 silhouette with Jordan appears with chukka boot inspiration with fashion-forward details, like olive suede paneling, metal D-ring eyelets and a snakeskin embossed leather along the toe. Westbrook’s initials appear on the brass lace deubré, while the white vulcanized midsole adds a lifestyle appeal.

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Retro High 'Rare Air'
results.story: The ‘Rare Air’ version of the Air Jordan 1 Retro High appears with an elegant makeup that features a combination of black pebbled and smooth leather panels throughout the upper construction. Bronze accents appear on the contrasting details, like the branding, collar and outsole, while the Nike Air logo on the tongue is replaced with a Jumpman icon that’s applied with a Velcro patch. The Wings logo is replaced with AIR JORDAN on the side, this shoe was inspired by an early prototype sample seen in a photo shoot from Jordan’s rookie year.

results.name: Jordan Westbrook 0 'Black'
results.story: With this Jordan Westbrook 0 release from September 2015, Russell Westbrook’s first off-court silhouette takes on a sleek all-black color scheme. The mid-top features a premium leather upper, complemented by a reptilian-texture overlay and a partially translucent midsole. Exterior branding elements include an embossed Jumpman on the tongue and a metallic gold lace jewel.

results.name: Air Jordan 6 Retro Low GP 'Sport Fuchsia'
Air Jordan 1 Retro High BG 'Blue Lagoon'
Air Jordan 7 Retro PS 'Marvin the Martian'
results.story: The Air Jordan 7 Retro PS 'Marvin the Martian' features a black leather upper with perforations on the sidewall and ankle for breathability. The sneaker also sports University Red accents on the Jumpman logo, forefoot, and on the traction-forward sole unit. The colors are inspired by the popular cartoon character from Mars.

results.name: Air Jordan 7 Retro BT 'Marvin The Martian'
Air Jordan 7 Retro TD Gift Pack 'Black Sport Fuchsia'
AJKO 'Chicago' 2015
results.story: The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG KO 2015 is a reissue of the original colorway in black, Varsity Red and white. Featuring an all-canvas build, the Jordan 1 KO is adorned with a Nike-branded tongue tag and a modified ‘Wings’ logo on the collar flap. The high-top is finished with white and red tooling borrowed from the Nike Vandal.

results.name: Air Jordan 7 Retro Gift Pack TD 'Bordeaux' 2015
Air Jordan 7 Retro PS 'Bordeaux' 2015
results.story: One of the original colors of the Air Jordan 7, the ‘Bordeaux’ iteration of the AJ7 pre-school appears in a classic grey and black color scheme on the upper’s nubuck paneling. The geometric pattern on the tongue is complemented with Bordeaux accents on the heel and Jumpman branding.

results.name: Jordan Westbrook 0 'Black'
results.story: Created for off-court wear, the Jordan Westbrook 0 is finished with an all-black upper, featuring a full-grain leather construction with raised lines inspired by the Air Jordan 11. An embossed crocodile texture is featured near the midsole, while the contrasting white autoclave sole unit features a siped outsole for flexibility. Russell Westbrook’s personal ‘Why Not?’ motto is embossed on the shoe’s gold lace jewels.

results.name: Jordan Westbrook 0
results.story: Jordan Brand athlete Russell Westbrook gets his own signature lifestyle Jordan offering, featuring the Westbrook 0. Constructed with a premium white leather makeup on the upper, the sneaker features a mid-top design with a unique triangular eyelet system. Contrasted with a gold lace dubrae, the shoe also sits on a vulcanized midsole for a casual aesthetic.

results.name: Air Jordan 7 Retro Gift Pack CB 'Hot Lava'
Jordan Westbrook 0
results.story: Russell Westbrook’s 0 silhouette with Jordan Brand is a lifestyle take on the brand’s long-standing basketball heritage. Featuring a chukka boot aesthetic that sports a vibrant Gym Red hue on the upper’s premium leather construction, the tongue implements a suede application, while the mudguard and toe are embossed with a faint crocodile print. The eyestay is equipped with triangular eyelets, while a vulcanized midsole is featured underfoot.

results.name: Jordan Jasmine GS
results.story: The Jordan Jasmine was inspired by Michael Jordan’s daughter, featuring a lifestyle-inspired high-top that’s formed with white tumbled leather. The mudguard is finished with a suede application, while gold Jordan and ‘Wings’ logos are displayed on the tongue and ankle. The shoe sits on a white vulcanized midsole.

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG 'Shattered Backboard' Sample
results.story: Inspired by Michael Jordan shattering a backboard during a Nike exhibition game in Italy in 1985, the ‘Shattered Backboard’ rendition of the Jordan 1 incorporates the black and orange color scheme from the uniform Jordan wore during the game. Sail accents on the quarter panel give the shoe a retro look, while the insole is stamped with a shattered backboard graphic.

results.name: Jordan Spizike BG
results.story: This retro release of the 2006 Jordan Spizike comes in boys sizing in a classic colorway including Jordan’s signature elephant print. The Spizike combines elements of several Jordan silhouettes that Mars Blackmon has advertised, including the Jordan 3, 4, 5, 6 and 20. The sneaker receives its name from film director Spike Lee, a long time ambassador of the Jordan Brand.

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG 'Chicago' 2015 Sample
Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG 'Pinnacle' Sample
Jordan Son Of Mars Low 'Pro Stars'
Air Jordan 13 Retro PS 'Barons'
results.story: In 2014, Jordan Brand released an Air Jordan 1 Retro 'Barons' and an Air Jordan 9 'Barons,' both inspired by Jordan's time in baseball's minor leagues with Alabama’s Birmingham Barons. This Air Jordan 13 Retro 'Barons' dropped six months later. It was the first Air Jordan 13 to feature an iridescent patent leather mudguard. This infant-sized version also sports white quilted leather overlays and Wolf Grey tumbled leather at the toe.

results.name: Air Jordan Future Low 'Photo Blue'
results.story: Released in Spring 2015, the Jordan Future Low ‘Photo Blue’ sneaker makes a bright statement. The color is reminiscent of UNC’s team colors, where Michael Jordan played during college. This Jordan shoe is made with an allover mesh upper and features lightweight cushioning for a breathable feel with plush comfort. Asymmetrical laces realized in blue are offset by a lace panel trimmed with a black border. A contrasting white rubber sole reinforces the design.

results.name: Air Jordan 4 Retro BT 'Teal'
results.story: With classic elements, the Air Jordan 4 Retro BT packages the legendary history of the 1989 icon for first walkers. This 'Teal' kids' iteration—introduced in March 2015—applies an old-school color scheme on the leather upper, mesh inserts and quarter cage. Contrast laces provide lightweight containment, while a matching mudguard offers reinforcement. The bicolor midsole and multicolored rubber outsole mimic the look of the adult original.

results.name: Air Jordan 7 Retro Gift Pack Infant 'Barcelona Nights'
Air Jordan 1 Retro Low 'Triple White'
results.story: The Air Jordan 1 has been termed ‘the sneaker that started it all,’ and this simple Triple White colorway can be viewed as something of a clean slate for the historic model. This low-top leather build is mostly true to the original high-top silhouette, with minor revisions in terms of branding: the OG ‘Wings’ logo is now embroidered on the heel, and a tonal Jumpman graces the lightly padded nylon tongue.

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Retro High BG 'Blake Griffin'
Air Jordan 7 Retro BP 'French Blue'
results.story: Styled for growing feet, the kids’ edition of the Air Jordan 7 Retro 'French Blue' sneaker makes a retro return—sporting the same specs as the 2015 remastered version that updated the OG 2002 colorway. This kids’ sneaker features the same premium leather upper upgrade with University Blue and Flint Grey accents throughout.

results.name: Jordan CP3.IX 'China'
results.story: Chris Paul’s ninth signature sneaker debuted two premier colorways in 2015, including this ‘China Emerald’ iteration. Distinguished by a jagged upper and midsole, the design pairs tonal green colors with black layers and metallic silver details. Signature elements include a dragon on the heel and Chinese characters on the outsole.

results.name: PSNY x Air Jordan 12 Retro 'Friends and Family'

Jordan 7 Retro TD Cleat 'Black White'
results.story: The Air Jordan 7 Retro TD Cleats bring a Jordan heritage silhouette to the gridiron. An all-black leather upper features the same layered look as the original, complete with a neoprene interior bootie topped with the AJ7’s signature tongue design. Instead of an Air Sole unit, the midsole features Nike Lunarlon foam, with a 12-cleat outsole configuration underfoot for quick directional changes.

results.name: Air Jordan 13 Retro GT 'Black Hyper Pink'
Air Jordan 1 Mid Nouveau 'Cool Grey'
results.story: Taking cues from various colorways of the Air Jordan line, specifically the AJ11 and AJ9, this exclusive 2014 mid-top updates the iconic Air Jordan 1. The Air Jordan 1 Mid Nouveau features a Cool Grey leather upper with perforations on the toe box and sidewall for breathability. The sneaker also sports a crisp white midsole with responsive cushioning, a contrasting gum rubber outsole, uniquely designed tongue tag, and debossed Wings branding at the ankle.

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Retro Low 'Gym Red'
results.story: First seen in 1985, the Air Jordan 1 was Michael Jordan's first signature sneaker and remains a classic as more iterations are released. Released in November 2014, the Air Jordan 1 Retro Low 'Gym Red’ takes after its high counterpart with original colors and branding. The Gym Red and black premium upper rests on the classic AJ1 white midsole and a black outsole.

results.name: Slam Dunk x Air Jordan 6 Retro 'Varsity Red'
Jordan Flight 9.5
results.story: The Jordan Flight 9.5 is a hybrid model that takes inspiration from various classic Air Jordan models to create a new off-court silhouette. The mid top’s white leather upper is accented with hits of Cool Grey on the lining and midsole, along with Sport Blue on the extra-tall padded tongue and rubber outsole.

results.name: CP3.VII AE
results.story: The Jordan CP3.VII Artisan Edition is an artistic take on Chris Paul’s signature model. Based in blue, the sneaker’s redesigned Hyperfuse upper is splashed with a multicolor paint splatter print under Dynamic Flywire cables. Underfoot, the textured Podulite tech Phylon midsole is contrasted in white and the herringbone outsole dons complementary colors of Sport Blue and Infrared.

results.name: Jordan Spizike BG 'Cool Grey Vibrant Yellow'
Air Jordan 14 Retro GP 'Hyper Pink'
results.story: Released in 2014, the Air Jordan 14 Retro GP features a design inspired by one of Michael Jordan's favorite car brands, Ferrari. Black and Metallic Dark Grey cover the majority of the shoe's leather and synthetic upper, while Hyper Pink accents appear on the Jordan signature details, lace loops and portions of the midsole and outsole. The low-cut model also features Zoom Air units in the heel and forefoot, a Phylon midsole and herringbone pattern on the outsole.

results.name: Air Jordan 14 Retro TD 'Hyper Pink'
results.story: The Air Jordan 14 Retro Infant features a leather and synthetic upper coated in grey and black with pink and white accents located throughout. Released in 2014, the low-cut sneaker's design draws inspiration from Ferrari and comes with prominent Jumpman branding, an asymmetrical collar and lace loops. Jordan's famous number 23 is displayed on the heel with a white non-marking outsole providing contrast and completing the look.

results.name: Air Jordan 6 Retro 'Brazil'
results.story: Designed by Tinker Hatfield, the Air Jordan 6 was worn by Michael Jordan during the 1990-91 NBA season en route to his first NBA championship ring. Released ahead of the 2014 FIFA World Cup in Brazil, the Air Jordan 6 Retro ‘Brazil' features a black nubuck and leather upper with green and yellow accents inspired by the Brazilian flag. The design also includes perforated detailing on the upper and speckled detailing on the midsole.

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Retro Low 'White Sport Blue'
Jordan Melo M10
results.story: Jordan Brand’s Melo M10 is the 10th Jumpman sneaker made for Carmelo Anthony. The Jordan 28-inspired sole includes the brand’s signature Flight Plate, while the bright red and black colorway suggests inspiration from the Chicago Bulls. The design is finished off with a chrome heel plate that spells out ‘Melo.’

results.name: Jordan Jumpman Team 1
results.story: Following in the footsteps of iconic Michael Jordan basketball sneakers, the 1997 Nike Jordan Jumpman Team 1 made a comeback with an April 2014 re-release. The classic court shoe is constructed of leather and nubuck overlays with paneled wavy design lines, a look reminiscent of the Air Jordan 12. The upper is reinforced by a textured heel tab and supportive lacing system. Bold Air Jumpman branding completes the retro, yet contemporary look.

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Retro Mid 'Dark Concord'
results.story: The Air Jordan 1 Retro Mid ‘Dark Concord’ features a mixed-material build finished with a straightforward two-tone colorway. The mid-top uses black nylon on the toe box and quarter panel, accented with Dark Concord leather overlays and a black leather Swoosh. Jumpman branding adorns the shoe’s heel panel as well as the tongue tag that graces the lightly padded nylon tongue.

results.name: Jordan Super.Fly 2 PO
results.story: Incorporating the ‘Infrared 23’ color scheme throughout its makeup, the Jordan Super.Fly 2 PO features a black mesh upper with Infrared tones highlighting the tongue, Jumpman branding and laces. Flywire cables on the eyestay complement the inner bootie system, while FlightPlate technology is included in the midsole.

results.name: Jordan Melo M10 Mid 'Black Atomic Mango'
Air Jordan CP3.VII AE
results.story: Chris Paul collaborated with Jordan Brand to continue his Jekyll & Hyde themed colorways. The Air Jordan CP3.VII AE features a mesh-based black upper with multi-color Flywire technology on the laces for support. The sneaker also sports a radio wave-type graphic on the heel dressed in a primarily purple color scheme, a black mesh tongue for breathability and comfort, and a cushioning midsole.

results.name: Air Jordan Future Premium 'Glow'
results.story: The Air Jordan Future Premium 'Glow' features a woven textile upper threaded with reflective 3M stitching. An asymmetrical lacing system curves across the forefoot to lend the shoe a snug fit, while gold tipped laces add contrast. The translucent foam sole, complete with a supportive midfoot shank, glows neon green in the dark. Jumpman branding is debossed on the leather tongue patch.

results.name: Air Jordan 6 Retro BP 'Infrared' 2014
results.story: The Air Jordan 6 Retro was first introduced by Michael Jordan en route to his first championship victory in 1991. Resurrected in November 2014 for its 23rd anniversary, this 'Infrared' kids' sneaker is rendered in nubuck with perforated panels. Its innovative tongue is secured by a quick-pull lacing system accented by a Jumpman lace lock. This instant classic sits on an infrared and white sole.

results.name: Jordan Flight 45 High
results.story: Nike revamped the Air Jordan Flight 45 with an all-red color scheme in 2014. Often compared to the Air Jordan 3, the upper construction and midfoot strap pair multiple shades of red. It’s midsole, borrowed from the AJ 3, stands out in contrasting white and black against the tonal look up top.

results.name: Air Jordan 6 Rings 'Elephant'
results.story: Dressed in black, Atomic Orange, New Slate and Wolf Grey, the Air Jordan 6 Rings 'Elephant' was released in January 2014. The silhouette combines elements from the seven Air Jordan models sported by MJ as his Chicago Bulls captured six NBA championships in the 1990s. This iteration comes with Jordan signature detailing and a mesh and leather upper that showcases the iconic elephant print on the overlay. Completing the look is a rubber outsole designed to provide traction on and off the court.

Jordan 6 Rings GS 'Hornets'
results.story: This grade school rendition of the Jordan 6 Rings ‘Hornets’ features a colorway inspired by the Charlotte NBA franchise. The primarily black leather construction on the upper sports teal and yellow contrasting throughout. The sneaker also borrows design elements from the Jordan 8, including the dual-strap fastening system and the chenille Jumpman logo seen on the tongue.

results.name: CP3.VII 'Bel Air'
results.story: Chris Paul teamed up with the Jordan Brand to develop the CP3.VII 'Bel Air' revealed in October 2013. Equipped with supportive and flexible Flywire technology and Zoom midsole, the shoe boasts multidirectional traction underfoot. The 1980s-inspired neon colorway accents a black, perforated upper while a 'VIN' number on the sole represents Paul's two children. 'Every time I lace my shoes up,' Paul says, 'I want to feel like I'm taking my family with me.'

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Retro '89 GS 'Black Fire Red Cement'
Air Jordan 8 Retro GS 'Playoff' 2013
results.story: Dropping in 2013, the Air Jordan 8 Retro GS 'Playoff' 2013 sneaker was released in homage to the 20th anniversary of the 1993 NBA Finals. The children’s interpretation of the adult shoe features a black nubuck upper supported by integrated straps with Nike Air Jordan branding and the number '23,' Michael Jordan’s iconic jersey number with the Chicago Bulls. Its mudguard is adorned with a brushstroke graphic similar to the 1993 ‘Playoff’ shoe.

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG 'Black Toe' 2013 Sample
Air Jordan 9 'Photo Blue' Black Bottom
results.story: The original ‘Photo Blue’ edition of the Air Jordan 9, which dropped in 2012, featured a white outsole. However, an alleged factory error resulted in pairs of the shoe being produced with a black outsole. Not wanting to scrap the unexpected colorway, Nike repurposed it as the ‘Black Bottom’ and released it a year later on Nike.com. Whether a true story or not, both ‘Photo Blue’ AJ9s pair a black upper with blue accents, but only this one boasts a black bottom.

results.name: Jordan Melo M9 'Knicks'
results.story: Carmelo Anthony’s ninth signature shoe with Jordan brand sports the New York Knicks team colors, featuring a combination of smooth and patent leather paneling throughout the upper, while the mesh tongue promotes breathability. The cross-weave overlays on the side panels work themselves up from the midsole to the eyelets to provide lateral forefoot support, and the inner bootie system is included for a personalized fit.

results.name: Jordan CP3.VI AE 'Squadron Green'
results.story: Jordan Brand released a fresh Artisan Edition of the CP3. The Jordan CP3.VI AE 'Squadron Green' features a mesh-based upper in an all-over Squadron Green color scheme for a military-inspired look. The sneaker also boasts fin-like details along the side wall and heel in patent leather, a breathable wrap-around tongue for an easy and comfortable fit, the classic Jumpman logo in black at the heel side, and a contrasting white traction-forward outsole.

results.name: Jordan Flight Luminary 'Cool Grey Bright Citrus'
Air Jordan 8 Retro 'Bugs Bunny' 2013
results.story: Jordan Brand celebrated the 20th anniversary of the Air Jordan 8 with a retro of the iconic 1993 home colorway worn by Michael Jordan during the 1992-1993 NBA season. Released in April 2013, the sneaker has been nicknamed the 'Bugs Bunny' after the 1990s commercial campaign starring MJ and the Looney Tunes character.

results.name: CP3.VII AE
results.story: Chris Paul’s third signature sneaker, the Jordan CP3.VI AE (Artisan Edition), debuted three new colorways in 2013 including this Neo Turquoise and black option. The futuristic silhouette features a black-based leather and mesh combination upper with contrast stitching and blue accents at the eyelets, liner, heel tab, and mini Jumpman logos. Underfoot, the blue hue also highlights Podulon tech which delivers area-specific comfort and responsiveness.

CP3.VI 'Team Orange'
results.story: The ‘Team Orange’ iteration of the Jordan CP3.IV was added to Chris Paul’s signature lineup in 2013. The design features a Hyperfuse upper with a diamond-patterned grid for lightness and breathability, a Phylon midsole, and a CP-exclusive outsole combination designed for responsiveness and quick cuts. Signature details include triangle shapes that pay homage to Paul’s grandfather, dots on the left heel representing his wedding date, and dots on the right heel representing his son’s birthday.

Jordan Legend TR 'Red Black'
results.story: Nike added another silhouette to Jordan Brand's expanding trainer collection with the release of the Jordan Legend TR 'Red Black' sneaker. Dropped in November 2012, the mid-top features a lightweight mesh inner sleeve, reinforced with exterior overlays and midfoot panels that integrate into the lacing system. The upper sits above a rubber outsole fitted with multi-directional traction and flex grooves, suited for indoor or outdoor performance.

results.name: Jordan Melo M8 Advance 'Game Royal'
results.story: Part of Carmelo Anthony’s two-shoe Home & Away pack, the Jordan Melo M8 Advance 'Game Royal' sneaker builds upon the M8 silhouette with upgraded design and performance. Released in October 2012, the basketball shoe is constructed of a Hyperfuse upper, improving the M8’s breathability and overall fit. The sole is fitted with a heel Air unit and Zoom Air in forefoot for cushioned comfort. New York Knicks away colors complete the design.

results.name: Jordan Melo M8 Advance 'Game Royal Team Orange'
Jordan 7 Retro PS 'Golden Moments'
results.story: In 1992, Michael Jordan led the United States basketball team to the gold medal at the Summer Olympics in Barcelona. To celebrate the 20th anniversary of the historic campaign, Jordan Brand released the ‘Golden Moments’ edition of the Air Jordan 7 in 2012. The sneaker features a leather and suede upper with hits of gold, while the the sockliner boasts a patriotic Stars and Stripes design. This is the preschool size version of the shoe.

results.name: Jordan Alpha Float Premier
results.story: The Jordan Alpha Float Premier features a patent black leather upper with a contrasting white forefoot. The slip-on also sports a Velcro brand closure for a personalized fit, the signature logo in black on the strap, a Jumpman logo in white on the side, and a bubble cushioning sole unit for long-lasting, durable comfort.

results.name: Undertow Design x Jordan Super.Fly 'Hit Rewindies Pack'
results.story: Portland-based brand Undertow teamed up with Jordan Brand to release an exclusive iteration of the Jordan Super.Fly silhouette. Drawing from the aesthetics of the 1990s, the Undertow Design x Jordan Super.Fly 'Hit Rewindies Pack' features a bright blue upper with black and white retro patterns on the collar and side. The sneaker also sports a tonal speckled midsole, a mesh tongue for breathability, and comes with a matching snapback hat and dress sock for a full 90s effect.

results.name: Air Jordan 17 Retro 'Rainbow'
results.story: This take on the Air Jordan 17 was an unreleased color sample first seen in 2012 as a part of the brand's rare 'Rainbow' collection. That pack featured every Air Jordan model created through 2011 with a tonal upper and its branding, laces and outsole in white. This shoe comes with Jumpman branding, a lace lock and musical notes on the laces overlay—a nod to jazz music being one of the design inspirations. Finishing the look is a herringbone pattern on the outsole to help with traction on and off the court.

results.name: Jordan Fly Wade 2 EV
results.story: This Miami Heat-inspired colorway of the Jordan Fly Wade 2 EV released in May 2012. Dwyane Wade’s second signature Nike shoe features a white synthetic upper supported by a TPU frame and Flywire cables in contrasting black. Additional hits of black appear on the tongue, Jumpman logo and midsole, which packs Lunarlon foam cushioning and a subtle pop of Gym Red.

results.name: Jordan CP3.V

results.story: Releasing in conjunction with Jordan’s Jekyll & Hyde pack for Chris Paul’s CP3.V silhouette, this shoe represents Paul’s less tenacious, off-court personality. Featuring a Wolf Grey exterior, the shoe is highlighted with vibrant shades of Bright Crimson, Electric Green and Violet Purple on the inner bootie system and heel pull-tab. The shoe released alongside an inverted colorway representing his on-court persona.

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Retro V.1 'Obsidian Varsity Red'
Air Jordan 2012 Q 'White Varsity Red'
results.story: Released in February 2012, the Air Jordan 2012 Q 'White Red Black' is a sneaker designed for basketball's quicker players. The shoe features a leather and synthetic upper supported by Flywire, a low-cut bootie and prominent Jumpman branding. Perforations on the toe box, side panel and heel promote breathability, while a 'Fly Around' insert, forefoot foam and Zoom Air help provide responsive cushioning. A modified patterned outsole assists with traction on and off the court.

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Phat GS 'Valentines Day'
results.story: Jordan Brand celebrates Valentine’s Day with a special grade-school rendition of the Jordan 1 Phat, featuring a metallic pink hue on the leather paneling and Swoosh. The overlays and eyestay are finished with a black suede application for contrast, while the underlay features a grey and white pattern. The festive effect is enhanced with a heart-shaped basketball logo on the heel.

results.name: Jordan CP3.V 'Black'
results.story: As Chris Paul’s fifth signature sneaker with Jordan Brand, the Air Jordan CP3.V 'Black' sneaker expands on the collection with upgraded design and performance. Released in January 2012, the basketball shoe is constructed of Flywire cables and innovative Hyperfuse; a three-layer material delivering stability, breathability and durability. Below, Podulon cushioning and Zoom Air help provide enhanced comfort and support.

results.name: Jordan X Auto Clave 'Bred'
results.story: The Auto Clave is a Jordan lifestyle offering that blends a series of heritage Jordan design elements with casual details to form a contemporary silhouette. Featuring a ‘Bred’ color scheme, the sneaker mirrors the aesthetic of the Jordan 10, implementing a tumbled leather construction with an asymmetrical lacing system. The vulcanized midsole is contrasted with the Air Jordan ‘Wings’ logo, while the Jumpman icon emerges on the collar.

results.name: Jordan Melo M8 'Christmas'
results.story: First seen on Carmelo Anthony playing with the New York Knicks against the Boston Celtics on Christmas Day 2011, the Jordan Melo M8 'Christmas' sneaker remixed the M8 silhouette to celebrate the NBA opening game. This version is dressed in smooth patent leather, accented with embossed design lines. The vivid mesh tongue and matching laces support the upper above, while the sole, equipped with visible Nike Air, reinforces the shoe underfoot.

results.name: Air Jordan 14 Retro GS 'Last Shot' 2011
results.story: Just before his second retirement, Michael Jordan wore a pair of Air Jordan 14 sneakers to win his final NBA title with the Bulls. The June 2018 Air Jordan 14 Retro GS 'Last Shot' sneaker is a detailed kids’ reproduction of the ’98 Tinker Hatfield-designed model. Styled for growing feet, it sports the same perforated Black and University Red leather upper from MJ’s game-winning shoe. A Jumpman logo on the yellow medallion and heel badge which is coupled with MJ’s #23 jersey number complete the retro-inspired design.

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Phat Low 'White Anthracite'
results.story: The Air Jordan 1 Phat Low 'White Anthracite' sneaker adds elevated details to the upgraded iteration of the original AJ1. Originally created with skaters in mind—who were already wearing the OG AJ1—the revamped Phat version features additional padding to help deliver enhanced comfort and durability. The White Anthracite version incorporates clean black borders lining the tongue, collar and outsole, the brand’s signature elephant print on the Swoosh logo and perforated details along the side panels.

results.name: Jordan Big Ups 'Bred'
results.story: The Jordan Big Ups 'Bred' features a black upper with a cutting-edge rib-cage style design for added structure and support. The sneaker also boasts black patent leather details, a mesh throat for breathability, and hits of Varsity Red. A large volume Max Air bag provides ample cushioning for this basketball silhouette.

results.name: Jordan Comfort Viz Air 13 'White Wolf Grey'
Jordan 7 Retro PS 'Bordeaux' 2011
results.story: This pre-school edition of the Jordan 7 Retro ‘Bordeaux’ is constructed with black and grey nubuck panels on the upper, while Bordeaux tones line the midsole, Jumpman branding and geometric pattern on the tongue. The AJ7 distinguished itself from previous Jordan offerings by eliminating the visible Air cushioning units and Nike branding while also being marketed separately from Nike Basketball.

results.name: Jordan Play In These 'White Varsity Red'
CMFT 11 Viz Air
results.story: Cool Grey returns to the Jordan 11, although this 11 isn’t the same one that Michael Jordan debuted back in 1995. The CMFT 11 Viz Air takes the upper of the classic basketball sneaker and converts it into a low-top offering that incorporates a premium leather mudguard with breathable mesh accents on the vamp. The hybrid Viz Air unit mirrors the design of an Air Max 1.

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Phat Low 'Elephant Print - Black'
Jordan Prime 5 'Varsity Red'
results.story: The Jordan Prime 5 blends design elements from the Jordan 5 and the Jordan 1, including the oversized tongue that’s lined with a 3M reflective finish, the lace-lock and the webbed side-paneling. The tonal Varsity Red hue appears throughout the leather upper, which includes a toe box similar to the Jordan 1, as well as on the Air-injected midsole.

results.name: Air Jordan 13 Retro PS 'Black Volt Cherry'
Air Jordan 3 Retro 'Doernbecher' 2010
results.story: The OHSU Doernbecher Children's Hospital in Portland, Oregon started a partnership with Nike in 2010 to allow admitted children and teenagers to design their very own footwear creations. The Air Jordan 3 Retro 'Doernbecher' 2010 was created by Cole Johanson. The sneaker features a red leather upper with “COLE” spelled out within the diamond grip pattern and callouts to his two favorites foods, spaghetti and chocolate, behind the pull tab. The sneaker also boasts black leather details throughout, an Air unit in the midsole for responsive cushioning, and “Strength and Courage” lettering on the insole as a nod to his lymphoma.

results.name: Jordan Comfort Max Air 12 'Black Medium Grey'
Air Jordan 1 Phat Low 'Black University Blue'
Air Jordan TE 2 Advance 'White Midnight Navy'
Air Jordan 9 Retro 'For The Love Of The Game'
results.story: Inspired by the team colors of the University of North Carolina, the Air Jordan 9 Retro 'For The Love Of The Game' sneaker pays tribute to Michael Jordan’s college hoops career which reinforced his love for basketball. Released in August 2010, Jordan’s ninth signature shoe comes dressed in Tar Heels colors, sporting a University Blue leather upper that’s surrounded by a patent White mudguard that extends to the heel. Jumpman logos at the midsole and heel counter complete this classic design.

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Phat Low 'Olympic'
results.story: The Air Jordan 1 Phat Low 'Olympic' sneaker offers a fresh take on the classic AJ1 silhouette with punches of color for a Fall 2010 release. Designed with skaters in mind, the ‘Phat’ model incorporates extra padding for enhanced comfort and durability. This interpretation features hits of primary colors—Green Bean, Varsity Red, New Blue and Yellow—covering the tongue lining, collar and stitching. The ‘Wings’ logo is seen in its usual red colorway, bringing a coincidental cohesiveness to the colorful design.
