Air Jordan Fusion 8 GS 'Varsity Maize'
results.story: The Air Jordan Fusion 8 GS released in 2010 with a color scheme of white, black, Varsity Maize and Stealth. The hybrid kids' shoe takes design cues from a pair of classic models, the Air Jordan 8 and Nike Air Force 1. Nods to the AJ8 include the sneaker's premium leather upper, Jumpman branding on the tongue and strapped-up design. Air Force 1 elements are present on the midsole and outsole, which are presented in black and white, respectively.

results.name: Air Jordan TE 2 Advance 'White Varsity Red'
Air Jordan Fusion 8 GP 'Bright Concord'
results.story: The Air Jordan Fusion 8 GP 'Bright Concord' combines elements from 1993's Air Jordan 8 and 1982's Nike Air Force 1. This kids' shoe, initially part of a gift pack that included a stocking hat, is a sized-down version of the adult model from 2010 presented in one of the OG AJ8 colorways—black, Bright Concord, Dark Charcoal and Aqua Tone. It features a premium upper, multicolored chenille Jumpman graphic on the tongue and crossover straps. Finishing the look is a Bright Concord outsole.

results.name: Air Jordan Fusion 8 GS 'Varsity Red'
results.story: Released in 2010, Air Jordan Fusion 8 GS is a kids' shoe that mixes elements from the sneaker Michael Jordan wore en route to his third NBA championship in 1993 with the iconic Nike Air Force 1. The sneaker comes with a black premium upper and AJ8-inspired features such as the tongue's fuzzy Jumpman branding and strap system which displays MJ's number 23. Varsity Red and Flint Grey accents, an AF1-like midsole and a durable multicolored outsole complete the style.

results.name: Air Jordan Fusion 8 'Varsity Red'
results.story: The Air Jordan Fusion 8 released in 2010 with design elements from two iconic sneakers, the Air Jordan 8 and the Nike Air Force 1. Presented with a black, Varsity Red and Flint Grey color scheme, the shoe comes with a few nods to the AJ 8, including its leather upper, chenille Jumpman on the tongue and supportive strap system. A multicolored overlay resides on the side of the heel atop a grey, AF 1-inspired midsole, while a durable red outsole completes the hybrid model.

results.name: Jordan 16.5 Team 'Varsity Red Taxi'
results.story: The Jordan Team 16.5 fuses the Air Jordan 16 and 17 with a black mesh-based upper. The mid top sports patent leather accents on the toe box, suede overlays on the side panel, Taxi details on the stitching and midsole, and Varsity Red accents on the eyelets, branding, and heel counter.

results.name: Jordan Spiz'ike PS 'Miami Vice'
results.story: Inspired by the vivid colors of Miami, this Jordan Spizike boasts a retro aesthetic with details from different commercials Spike Lee has done with Jordan Brand. The sneaker features a Clear Grey leather upper with mesh paneling on the side panel for breathability. The sneaker also boasts Neutral Grey leather accents on the upper mudguard, elephant print on the lower mudguard, Turbo Green details, and hits of Vivid Pink.

results.name: Air Jordan 7 Retro 'DMP'
results.story: This edition of the Air Jordan 7 was released as part of the Defining Moments Package. The collection comprised two colorways: one based on the uniform of the Toronto Raptors, the other on the Orlando Magic. This half of the pack, the Raptors half, features a black and charcoal nubuck upper with hits of red on the midsole and Jumpman emblem. A neoprene inner sleeve is marked with ‘JORDAN’ lettering on the tongue.

results.name: Air Jordan 3 Retro 'True Blue' 2009
results.story: The ‘True Blue’ Jordan 3 first saw a retro in 2003, and then again for this 2009 reissue. This version is mostly the same as before, with a Jumpman logo replacing the NIKE AIR on the heel. It also features a tumbled white leather upper, True Blue accents on the lining, molded eyelets and midsole, while a final contrasting pop of red appears on the Jumpman logo on the tongue.

results.name: Jordan 1 Flight Mid 'Chicago'
results.story: Appearing in the Chicago color scheme that originally debuted on the Air Jordan 1, the Jordan 1 Flight Mid is a lifestyle spin-off of the classic basketball sneaker, featuring a combination of red and white panels with patent and tumbled leather applications. Implementing a similar heel, quarter panel and eyelet formation as the Jordan 4, Jumpman logos are seen on the tongue and side panel.

results.name: Air Jordan Fusion 6 TD 'Varsity Red'
results.story: The Air Jordan Fusion 6 TD 'Varsity Red' mixes design elements from a pair of classic silhouettes, 1991's Air Jordan 6 and 1982's Nike Air Force 1. The kids' shoe released in 2009 with a color scheme of white, black and Varsity Red. Nods to the AJ 6 include its premium white upper, Jumpman branding and molded heel tab. An ankle strap, the Nike Swoosh on the quarter panel and the contrasting red midsole are among the sneaker's AF1-inspired elements.

results.name: Air Jordan Fusion 6 Premium 'BHM'
results.story: Nike continued their annual celebration of Black History Month with the release of this Air Jordan Fusion 6 Premium 'BHM' colorway in 2009. The special edition features black premium leather and canvas with an African-style quilt pattern across the side panels and toe box. A branded lace jewel and heel badge commemorate the occasion atop a black midsole and brown outsole.
